{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1773481721821,"sessionID":"ses_3144093abffe4EFLXWMouX7qVB","part":{"id":"prt_cebbf7c61001oX7LkxLVyeL8Jq","sessionID":"ses_3144093abffe4EFLXWMouX7qVB","messageID":"msg_cebbf6c93001XBFnCRrG1MYmTc","type":"tool","callID":"toolu_vrtx_01YFQgQcWDCzrNsdDKaSkLri","tool":"read","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/fulgidus/Documents/wombo-combo-worktrees/wave-detach-audit/AGENTS.md"},"output":"<path>/home/fulgidus/Documents/wombo-combo-worktrees/wave-detach-audit/AGENTS.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>1: # AGENTS.md — Instructions for AI agents working on wombo-combo\n2: \n3: This file is for AI coding agents operating **on the wombo-combo codebase itself**.\n4: If you are an agent **using** wombo as a tool in another project, see CONTEXT.md instead.\n5: \n6: ---\n7: \n8: ## HARD CONSTRAINTS\n9: \n10: These are non-negotiable. Violating any of them will break the development workflow.\n11: \n12: ### 1. Always use `bun dev`, never the global binary\n13: \n14: ```\n15: # CORRECT — runs local source directly\n16: bun dev <command> [args...]\n17: \n18: # WRONG — runs the globally installed (possibly stale) binary\n19: wombo <command> [args...]\n20: ```\n21: \n22: **Why:** wombo is dogfooded — we develop it using itself. The global binary is a\n23: snapshot from the last release. If you use it, you're testing old code, not your\n24: changes. `bun dev` runs `bun src/index.ts` which executes the current working tree.\n25: \n26: **Examples:**\n27: ```sh\n28: bun dev help\n29: bun dev tasks list\n30: bun dev tasks add my-feat \"My Feature\" --priority high\n31: bun dev launch --dry-run --all-ready\n32: bun dev init --force\n33: ```\n34: \n35: ### 2. Never publish to npm\n36: \n37: Distribution is GitHub-only. Users install via:\n38: ```sh\n39: bun install -g github:fulgidus/wombo\n40: ```\n41: Do not add `publishConfig`, do not run `npm publish`, do not add `.npmrc`.\n42: \n43: ### 3. Keep bun.lock committed\n44: \n45: The lockfile is committed for reproducible installs from GitHub. Always commit\n46: `bun.lock` after adding/removing/updating dependencies.\n47: \n48: ### 4. Do not commit user artifacts\n49: \n50: All wombo-combo user artifacts live under `.wombo-combo/` (config, tasks, archive,\n51: state, logs, history). This directory is gitignored.\n52: \n53: The template at `src/templates/tasks.yml` is the canonical source for the task\n54: file schema. The root `.wombo-combo/` dir is for local development only.\n55: \n56: ---\n57: \n58: ## Project structure\n59: \n60: ```\n61: wombo/\n62:   package.json              # name: wombo-combo, version in sync with git tags\n63:   src/\n64:     index.ts                # CLI entry point, arg parsing, command routing\n65:     config.ts               # WomboConfig type, defaults, loader, validator\n66:     commands/\n67:       init.ts               # Interactive guided setup (Prompter class)\n68:       launch.ts             # Launch a wave of agents\n69:       resume.ts             # Resume a stopped wave\n70:       status.ts             # Show wave status\n71:       verify.ts             # Build verification\n72:       merge.ts              # Merge verified branches\n73:       retry.ts              # Retry a failed agent\n74:       cleanup.ts            # Remove worktrees and sessions\n75:       tasks/\n76:         list.ts, add.ts, set-status.ts, check.ts, archive.ts, show.ts\n77:     lib/\n78:       tasks.ts              # Task file I/O, types, ensureTasksFile guard\n79:       state.ts              # Wave state persistence\n80:       prompt.ts             # Agent prompt generation\n81:       launcher.ts           # Process spawning\n82:       monitor.ts            # ProcessMonitor\n83:       worktree.ts           # Git worktree management\n84:       merger.ts             # Git merge operations\n85:       verifier.ts           # Build verification logic\n86:       ui.ts                 # Console dashboard\n87:       tui.ts                # neo-blessed TUI\n88:     templates/\n89:       tasks.yml             # Template with full schema docs\n90: ```\n91: \n92: ## User-facing file layout\n93: \n94: All wombo-combo files live under `.wombo-combo/`:\n95: \n96: ```\n97: .wombo-combo/\n98:   config.json     # Project configuration (replaces wombo.json)\n99:   tasks.yml       # Active tasks (replaces .features.yml)\n100:   archive.yml     # Completed/cancelled tasks\n101:   state.json      # Wave state\n102:   logs/           # Agent log files\n103:   history/        # Wave history records\n104: ```\n105: \n106: ## Coding conventions\n107: \n108: - **Runtime:** Bun (not Node). Use Bun APIs where available (`Bun.file()`,\n109:   `Bun.spawn()`, etc.), fall back to Node stdlib when Bun doesn't have a\n110:   direct equivalent.\n111: - **Language:** TypeScript, strict mode. Run `bun run typecheck` to verify.\n112: - **Modules:** ESM only (`\"type\": \"module\"` in package.json). Use `.js`\n113:   extensions in import paths (TypeScript resolves them to `.ts` at runtime in Bun).\n114: - **No external CLI frameworks.** Arg parsing is hand-rolled in `index.ts`.\n115:   This is intentional — it keeps the dependency tree minimal and gives full\n116:   control for agent-readiness features (schema introspection, etc.).\n117: - **YAML library:** `yaml` (v2). Use `YAML.parse()` / `YAML.stringify()`.\n118: - **No npm registry dependencies** for core functionality. `neo-blessed` is\n119:   the only large dependency (TUI). Keep it that way.\n120: \n121: ## Testing and verification\n122: \n123: ```sh\n124: # Type check (no emit)\n125: bun run typecheck\n126: \n127: # Build (outputs to dist/)\n128: bun run build\n129: \n130: # Run any command via dev\n131: bun dev help\n132: bun dev tasks check\n133: ```\n134: \n135: There is no test suite yet. When adding tests, use Bun's built-in test runner\n136: (`bun test`).\n137: \n138: ## Known quirks\n139: \n140: - **Bun readline + piped stdin:** `rl.question()` silently fails after readline\n141:   emits `close`. The `Prompter` class in `src/commands/init.ts` works around\n142:   this using `rl[Symbol.asyncIterator]()` with `process.stdout.write()`.\n143: - **YAML null vs empty array:** `yaml` parses `tasks:` (no items) as `null`,\n144:   not `[]`. `loadTasks()` normalizes this: `parsed.tasks ?? parsed.features ?? null`.\n145: - **`import.meta.dir`:** Gives the directory of the current source file in Bun.\n146:   Used in `src/lib/tasks.ts` to resolve the template path.\n147: \n148: ## Feature backlog\n149: \n150: The active backlog lives in `.wombo-combo/tasks.yml` (local, gitignored). Use\n151: `bun dev tasks list` to see it. The canonical template is at\n152: `src/templates/tasks.yml`.\n153: \n154: ## Making changes\n155: \n156: 1. **Check the backlog:** `bun dev tasks list`\n157: 2. **Pick a feature/subtask:** `bun dev tasks show <id>`\n158: 3. **Mark it in-progress:** `bun dev tasks set-status <id> in_progress`\n159: 4. **Implement the change**\n160: 5. **Typecheck:** `bun run typecheck`\n161: 6. **Build:** `bun run build`\n162: 7. **Test manually:** `bun dev <relevant-command>`\n163: 8. **Mark done:** `bun dev tasks set-status <id> done`\n164: 9. **Commit** with a conventional commit message referencing the feature ID\n165: \n166: ## Version and release\n167: \n168: - Current version is in `package.json` → `\"version\"` field.\n169: - Git tags must match: tag `v0.1.0` ↔ `\"version\": \"0.1.0\"`.\n170: - **When creating a git tag, ALWAYS update `package.json` `\"version\"` first,\n171:   commit the bump, then tag that commit.** Never tag without bumping the\n172:   version — they must stay in sync.\n173: - Release workflow (when implemented) triggers on `v*` tag push to main.\n\n(End of file - total 173 lines)\n</content>","title":"AGENTS.md","metadata":{"preview":"# AGENTS.md — Instructions for AI agents working on wombo-combo\n\nThis file is for AI coding agents operating **on the wombo-combo codebase itself**.\nIf you are an agent **using** wombo as a tool in another project, see CONTEXT.md instead.\n\n---\n\n## HARD CONSTRAINTS\n\nThese are non-negotiable. Violating any of them will break the development workflow.\n\n### 1. Always use `bun dev`, never the global binary\n\n```\n# CORRECT — runs local source directly\nbun dev <command> [args...]\n\n# WRONG — runs the globally installed (possibly stale) binary\nwombo <command> [args...]\n```","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"time":{"start":1773481721814,"end":1773481721820}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1773481722364,"sessionID":"ses_3144093abffe4EFLXWMouX7qVB","part":{"id":"prt_cebbf7fd80011OlNtg8OCA1JQi","sessionID":"ses_3144093abffe4EFLXWMouX7qVB","messageID":"msg_cebbf6c93001XBFnCRrG1MYmTc","type":"tool","callID":"toolu_vrtx_01V2xPf1SGMYeizkcfnSKmT7","tool":"read","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/fulgidus/Documents/wombo-combo-worktrees/wave-detach-audit/src/lib/launcher.ts"},"output":"<path>/home/fulgidus/Documents/wombo-combo-worktrees/wave-detach-audit/src/lib/launcher.ts</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>1: /**\n2:  * launcher.ts — Process spawning and terminal multiplexer session management.\n3:  *\n4:  * Responsibilities:\n5:  *   - Launch agent in headless mode (agent run --format json)\n6:  *   - Launch agent in interactive mode (dmux/tmux session with TUI)\n7:  *   - Resume sessions for auto-retry\n8:  *   - Manage multiplexer sessions (create, list, kill)\n9:  *\n10:  * Supports both dmux (preferred) and tmux (fallback) via the multiplexer\n11:  * abstraction layer. The active backend is determined by config.agent.multiplexer.\n12:  */\n13: \n14: import { spawn, execSync, type ChildProcess } from \"node:child_process\";\n15: import { writeFileSync, unlinkSync } from \"node:fs\";\n16: import type { WomboConfig } from \"../config.js\";\n17: import { resolveAgentBin } from \"../config.js\";\n18: import {\n19:   detectMultiplexer,\n20:   muxNewSession,\n21:   muxHasSession,\n22:   muxKillSession,\n23:   muxListSessions,\n24:   muxGetPanePid,\n25:   muxLoadBuffer,\n26:   muxPasteBuffer,\n27:   muxSendKeys,\n28:   muxDisplayName,\n29:   type MultiplexerInfo,\n30: } from \"./multiplexer.js\";\n31: import { portlessEnv } from \"./portless.js\";\n32: import { hitlDir } from \"./hitl-channel.js\";\n33: import { resolve, dirname } from \"node:path\";\n34: \n35: // ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n36: // Types\n37: // ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n38: \n39: export interface LaunchResult {\n40:   pid: number;\n41:   process: ChildProcess;\n42:   sessionId?: string;\n43: }\n44: \n45: export interface LaunchOptions {\n46:   worktreePath: string;\n47:   featureId: string;\n48:   prompt: string;\n49:   model?: string;\n50:   interactive?: boolean;\n51:   config: WomboConfig;\n52:   /** Override the agent name (for specialized agents from the registry) */\n53:   agentName?: string;\n54:   /** HITL mode for this agent (from quest or config) */\n55:   hitlMode?: string;\n56:   /** Project root (for HITL directory path) */\n57:   projectRoot?: string;\n58: }\n59: \n60: export interface RetryOptions {\n61:   worktreePath: string;\n62:   featureId: string;\n63:   sessionId: string;\n64:   buildErrors: string;\n65:   model?: string;\n66:   interactive?: boolean;\n67:   config: WomboConfig;\n68:   /** HITL mode for this agent (from quest or config) */\n69:   hitlMode?: string;\n70:   /** Project root (for HITL directory path) */\n71:   projectRoot?: string;\n72: }\n73: \n74: // ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n75: // Helpers\n76: // ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n77: \n78: function muxSessionName(featureId: string, config: WomboConfig): string {\n79:   return `${config.agent.tmuxPrefix}-${featureId}`;\n80: }\n81: \n82: /**\n83:  * Get the multiplexer info for this config.\n84:  * Caches detection per-process.\n85:  */\n86: function getMux(config: WomboConfig): MultiplexerInfo {\n87:   return detectMultiplexer(config.agent.multiplexer);\n88: }\n89: \n90: function runSilent(cmd: string): string {\n91:   try {\n92:     return execSync(cmd, { encoding: \"utf-8\", stdio: \"pipe\" }).trim();\n93:   } catch {\n94:     return \"\";\n95:   }\n96: }\n97: \n98: /**\n99:  * Build environment variables for an agent process.\n100:  * Merges process.env with OPENCODE_DIR, portless env vars, and HITL env vars.\n101:  */\n102: function agentEnv(\n103:   worktreePath: string,\n104:   featureId: string,\n105:   config: WomboConfig,\n106:   hitlMode?: string,\n107:   projectRoot?: string\n108: ): Record<string, string | undefined> {\n109:   const env: Record<string, string | undefined> = {\n110:     ...process.env,\n111:     OPENCODE_DIR: worktreePath,\n112:     ...portlessEnv(featureId, config),\n113:   };\n114: \n115:   // HITL environment — always set so the hitl-ask script is available,\n116:   // but the prompt controls whether the agent actually uses it.\n117:   if (projectRoot) {\n118:     env.WOMBO_HITL_DIR = hitlDir(projectRoot);\n119:     env.WOMBO_AGENT_ID = featureId;\n120:     env.WOMBO_HITL_MODE = hitlMode ?? \"yolo\";\n121:     // Path to the hitl-ask script (relative to this module)\n122:     // In development: src/lib/hitl-ask.ts\n123:     // In production (bundled): same dir as this file\n124:     const hitlAskPath = resolve(import.meta.dir, \"hitl-ask.ts\");\n125:     env.WOMBO_HITL_ASK = hitlAskPath;\n126:   }\n127: \n128:   return env;\n129: }\n130: \n131: // ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n132: // Headless Launch\n133: // ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n134: \n135: /**\n136:  * Launch agent in headless mode with JSON output.\n137:  */\n138: export function launchHeadless(opts: LaunchOptions): LaunchResult {\n139:   const agentBin = resolveAgentBin(opts.config);\n140: \n141:   const args = [\n142:     \"run\",\n143:     \"--format\", \"json\",\n144:     \"--agent\", opts.agentName ?? opts.config.agent.name,\n145:     \"--dir\", opts.worktreePath,\n146:     \"--title\", `woco: ${opts.featureId}`,\n147:   ];\n148: \n149:   if (opts.model) {\n150:     args.push(\"--model\", opts.model);\n151:   }\n152: \n153:   args.push(opts.prompt);\n154: \n155:   const child = spawn(agentBin, args, {\n156:     stdio: [\"pipe\", \"pipe\", \"pipe\"],\n157:     detached: false,\n158:     env: agentEnv(opts.worktreePath, opts.featureId, opts.config, opts.hitlMode, opts.projectRoot),\n159:   });\n160: \n161:   // Close stdin so agent starts processing immediately\n162:   child.stdin?.end();\n163: \n164:   return {\n165:     pid: child.pid!,\n166:     process: child,\n167:   };\n168: }\n169: \n170: /**\n171:  * Resume a headless session with a retry message (build errors).\n172:  */\n173: export function retryHeadless(opts: RetryOptions): LaunchResult {\n174:   const agentBin = resolveAgentBin(opts.config);\n175: \n176:   const retryMessage = `The build failed. Please fix the following errors and run \\`${opts.config.build.command}\\` again:\\n\\n\\`\\`\\`\\n${opts.buildErrors}\\n\\`\\`\\`\\n\\nFix all errors, then verify the build passes.`;\n177: \n178:   const args = [\n179:     \"run\",\n180:     \"--format\", \"json\",\n181:     \"--session\", opts.sessionId,\n182:     \"--continue\",\n183:     \"--dir\", opts.worktreePath,\n184:   ];\n185: \n186:   if (opts.model) {\n187:     args.push(\"--model\", opts.model);\n188:   }\n189: \n190:   args.push(retryMessage);\n191: \n192:   const child = spawn(agentBin, args, {\n193:     stdio: [\"pipe\", \"pipe\", \"pipe\"],\n194:     detached: false,\n195:     env: agentEnv(opts.worktreePath, opts.featureId, opts.config, opts.hitlMode, opts.projectRoot),\n196:   });\n197: \n198:   child.stdin?.end();\n199: \n200:   return {\n201:     pid: child.pid!,\n202:     process: child,\n203:   };\n204: }\n205: \n206: // ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n207: // Conflict Resolution Launch\n208: // ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n209: \n210: export interface ConflictResolverOptions {\n211:   worktreePath: string;\n212:   featureId: string;\n213:   prompt: string;\n214:   model?: string;\n215:   config: WomboConfig;\n216:   /** Override the agent name for conflict resolution (default: merge-resolver-agent) */\n217:   agentName?: string;\n218: }\n219: \n220: /**\n221:  * Launch a headless agent to resolve merge conflicts.\n222:  *\n223:  * This is similar to `launchHeadless`, but the prompt is a conflict-resolution\n224:  * prompt generated by `generateConflictResolutionPrompt()`. The agent runs in\n225:  * the feature worktree where `git merge <baseBranch>` has already been run,\n226:  * leaving conflict markers in the working tree.\n227:  *\n228:  * By default uses the specialized \"merge-resolver-agent\" definition, which\n229:  * has minimal context and is focused solely on conflict resolution. Falls back\n230:  * to the generalist agent if no merge-resolver-agent is available.\n231:  */\n232: export function launchConflictResolver(opts: ConflictResolverOptions): LaunchResult {\n233:   const agentBin = resolveAgentBin(opts.config);\n234: \n235:   // Use the specialized merge-resolver agent by default\n236:   const agentName = opts.agentName ?? \"merge-resolver-agent\";\n237: \n238:   const args = [\n239:     \"run\",\n240:     \"--format\", \"json\",\n241:     \"--agent\", agentName,\n242:     \"--dir\", opts.worktreePath,\n243:     \"--title\", `woco: conflict-resolve ${opts.featureId}`,\n244:   ];\n245: \n246:   if (opts.model) {\n247:     args.push(\"--model\", opts.model);\n248:   }\n249: \n250:   args.push(opts.prompt);\n251: \n252:   const child = spawn(agentBin, args, {\n253:     stdio: [\"pipe\", \"pipe\", \"pipe\"],\n254:     detached: false,\n255:     env: agentEnv(opts.worktreePath, opts.featureId, opts.config),\n256:   });\n257: \n258:   child.stdin?.end();\n259: \n260:   return {\n261:     pid: child.pid!,\n262:     process: child,\n263:   };\n264: }\n265: \n266: // ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n267: // Interactive (multiplexer) Launch\n268: // ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n269: \n270: /**\n271:  * Launch agent in a terminal multiplexer session (dmux or tmux) for interactive use.\n272:  */\n273: export function launchInteractive(opts: LaunchOptions): LaunchResult {\n274:   const agentBin = resolveAgentBin(opts.config);\n275:   const mux = getMux(opts.config);\n276:   const sessionName = muxSessionName(opts.featureId, opts.config);\n277: \n278:   // Kill existing session if any\n279:   killMuxSession(opts.featureId, opts.config);\n280: \n281:   // Build the agent command to run inside the multiplexer\n282:   // Include portless env vars so any server started in the session\n283:   // is routed through the portless proxy\n284:   const pEnv = portlessEnv(opts.featureId, opts.config);\n285:   const envPrefix = Object.entries(pEnv)\n286:     .map(([k, v]) => `${k}=${JSON.stringify(v)}`)\n287:     .join(\" \");\n288: \n289:   const ocArgs = [\n290:     agentBin,\n291:     \"--dir\", JSON.stringify(opts.worktreePath),\n292:   ];\n293: \n294:   // Pass agent name if specified (specialized agent from registry or per-task override)\n295:   if (opts.agentName) {\n296:     ocArgs.push(\"--agent\", JSON.stringify(opts.agentName));\n297:   }\n298: \n299:   if (opts.model) {\n300:     ocArgs.push(\"--model\", JSON.stringify(opts.model));\n301:   }\n302: \n303:   const muxCmd = envPrefix ? `${envPrefix} ${ocArgs.join(\" \")}` : ocArgs.join(\" \");\n304: \n305:   // Create a detached session running the agent\n306:   muxNewSession(mux, sessionName, opts.worktreePath, muxCmd);\n307: \n308:   // Send the prompt as initial message after a brief delay\n309:   setTimeout(() => {\n310:     try {\n311:       const tmpFile = `/tmp/woco-prompt-${opts.featureId}.txt`;\n312:       writeFileSync(tmpFile, opts.prompt);\n313:       muxLoadBuffer(mux, tmpFile);\n314:       muxPasteBuffer(mux, sessionName);\n315:       muxSendKeys(mux, sessionName, \"Enter\");\n316:       try { unlinkSync(tmpFile); } catch {}\n317:     } catch {\n318:       // If prompt sending fails, user can type manually\n319:     }\n320:   }, 3000);\n321: \n322:   // Get the PID of the pane process\n323:   const panePid = muxGetPanePid(mux, sessionName);\n324: \n325:   return {\n326:     pid: panePid,\n327:     process: null as any, // No direct process handle in multiplexer mode\n328:   };\n329: }\n330: \n331: /**\n332:  * Resume an interactive session with retry message.\n333:  */\n334: export function retryInteractive(opts: RetryOptions): LaunchResult {\n335:   const mux = getMux(opts.config);\n336:   const sessionName = muxSessionName(opts.featureId, opts.config);\n337: \n338:   const exists = muxSessionExists(opts.featureId, opts.config);\n339: \n340:   if (exists) {\n341:     const retryMsg = `The build failed. Fix these errors:\\n${opts.buildErrors}`;\n342:     const tmpFile = `/tmp/woco-retry-${opts.featureId}.txt`;\n343:     writeFileSync(tmpFile, retryMsg);\n344:     muxLoadBuffer(mux, tmpFile);\n345:     muxPasteBuffer(mux, sessionName);\n346:     muxSendKeys(mux, sessionName, \"Enter\");\n347:     try { unlinkSync(tmpFile); } catch {}\n348: \n349:     const panePid = muxGetPanePid(mux, sessionName);\n350: \n351:     return {\n352:       pid: panePid,\n353:       process: null as any,\n354:     };\n355:   }\n356: \n357:   // Session doesn't exist — launch a new interactive session\n358:   return launchInteractive({\n359:     worktreePath: opts.worktreePath,\n360:     featureId: opts.featureId,\n361:     prompt: `Continue from session ${opts.sessionId}. The build failed:\\n${opts.buildErrors}\\n\\nFix all errors and verify the build passes.`,\n362:     model: opts.model,\n363:     interactive: true,\n364:     config: opts.config,\n365:   });\n366: }\n367: \n368: // ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n369: // Multiplexer Session Management\n370: // ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n371: \n372: /**\n373:  * Check if a multiplexer session exists for a feature.\n374:  */\n375: export function muxSessionExists(\n376:   featureId: string,\n377:   config: WomboConfig\n378: ): boolean {\n379:   const mux = getMux(config);\n380:   const sessionName = muxSessionName(featureId, config);\n381:   return muxHasSession(mux, sessionName);\n382: }\n383: \n384: /**\n385:  * Kill a multiplexer session for a feature.\n386:  */\n387: export function killMuxSession(\n388:   featureId: string,\n389:   config: WomboConfig\n390: ): void {\n391:   const mux = getMux(config);\n392:   const sessionName = muxSessionName(featureId, config);\n393:   muxKillSession(mux, sessionName);\n394: }\n395: \n396: /**\n397:  * List all woco-related multiplexer sessions.\n398:  */\n399: export function listMuxSessions(config: WomboConfig): string[] {\n400:   const mux = getMux(config);\n401:   const sessions = muxListSessions(mux);\n402:   return sessions.filter((s) => s.startsWith(config.agent.tmuxPrefix + \"-\"));\n403: }\n404: \n405: /**\n406:  * Kill all woco-related multiplexer sessions.\n407:  */\n408: export function killAllMuxSessions(config: WomboConfig): number {\n409:   const mux = getMux(config);\n410:   const sessions = listMuxSessions(config);\n411:   for (const s of sessions) {\n412:     muxKillSession(mux, s);\n413:   }\n414:   return sessions.length;\n415: }\n416: \n417: /**\n418:  * Get the display name of the active multiplexer backend.\n419:  */\n420: export function getMultiplexerName(config: WomboConfig): string {\n421:   try {\n422:     const mux = getMux(config);\n423:     return muxDisplayName(mux);\n424:   } catch {\n425:     return \"tmux/dmux\";\n426:   }\n427: }\n428: \n429: // ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n430: // Backward Compatibility Aliases\n431: // ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n432: \n433: /** @deprecated Use muxSessionExists instead */\n434: export const tmuxSessionExists = muxSessionExists;\n435: /** @deprecated Use killMuxSession instead */\n436: export const killTmuxSession = killMuxSession;\n437: /** @deprecated Use listMuxSessions instead */\n438: export const listTmuxSessions = listMuxSessions;\n439: /** @deprecated Use killAllMuxSessions instead */\n440: export const killAllTmuxSessions = killAllMuxSessions;\n441: \n442: /**\n443:  * Check if a process is still running by PID.\n444:  */\n445: export function isProcessRunning(pid: number): boolean {\n446:   if (!pid || pid <= 0) return false;\n447:   try {\n448:     process.kill(pid, 0);\n449:     return true;\n450:   } catch {\n451:     return false;\n452:   }\n453: }\n\n(End of file - total 453 lines)\n</content>","title":"src/lib/launcher.ts","metadata":{"preview":"/**\n * launcher.ts — Process spawning and terminal multiplexer session management.\n *\n * Responsibilities:\n *   - Launch agent in headless mode (agent run --format json)\n *   - Launch agent in interactive mode (dmux/tmux session with TUI)\n *   - Resume sessions for auto-retry\n *   - Manage multiplexer sessions (create, list, kill)\n *\n * Supports both dmux (preferred) and tmux (fallback) via the multiplexer\n * abstraction layer. The active backend is determined by config.agent.multiplexer.\n */\n\nimport { spawn, execSync, type ChildProcess } from \"node:child_process\";\nimport { writeFileSync, unlinkSync } from \"node:fs\";\nimport type { WomboConfig } from \"../config.js\";\nimport { resolveAgentBin } from \"../config.js\";\nimport {\n  detectMultiplexer,\n  muxNewSession,","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"time":{"start":1773481722360,"end":1773481722363}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1773481722749,"sessionID":"ses_3144093abffe4EFLXWMouX7qVB","part":{"id":"prt_cebbf81f90014hkk2yH9kZ5qjG","sessionID":"ses_3144093abffe4EFLXWMouX7qVB","messageID":"msg_cebbf6c93001XBFnCRrG1MYmTc","type":"tool","callID":"toolu_vrtx_01TFuLPBFUVcwh378RaEidKj","tool":"read","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/fulgidus/Documents/wombo-combo-worktrees/wave-detach-audit/src/lib/monitor.ts"},"output":"<path>/home/fulgidus/Documents/wombo-combo-worktrees/wave-detach-audit/src/lib/monitor.ts</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>1: /**\n2:  * monitor.ts — Parse JSON events from agent and detect completion/failure.\n3:  *\n4:  * Responsibilities:\n5:  *   - Parse newline-delimited JSON events from agent stdout\n6:  *   - Detect session completion (agent finished)\n7:  *   - Detect session ID from events\n8:  *   - Detect errors and failures\n9:  *   - Write per-agent raw log files for diagnostics\n10:  *   - Maintain per-agent parsed activity log for TUI preview\n11:  */\n12: \n13: import type { ChildProcess } from \"node:child_process\";\n14: import { isProcessRunning } from \"./launcher.js\";\n15: import { mkdirSync, appendFileSync, existsSync } from \"node:fs\";\n16: import { resolve } from \"node:path\";\n17: \n18: // ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n19: // Log directory name (configurable would be overkill here)\n20: // ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n21: \n22: const LOG_DIR_NAME = \".wombo-combo/logs\";\n23: \n24: // ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n25: // Types — OpenCode JSON Events\n26: // ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n27: \n28: export interface OpenCodeEvent {\n29:   type: string;\n30:   sessionID?: string;\n31:   timestamp?: number;\n32:   part?: {\n33:     type?: string;\n34:     tool?: string;\n35:     callID?: string;\n36:     text?: string;\n37:     reason?: string;\n38:     cost?: number;\n39:     tokens?: {\n40:       total: number;\n41:       input: number;\n42:       output: number;\n43:       reasoning: number;\n44:     };\n45:     state?: {\n46:       status?: string;\n47:       input?: Record<string, any>;\n48:       output?: string;\n49:       error?: string;\n50:     };\n51:   };\n52:   [key: string]: any;\n53: }\n54: \n55: // ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n56: // Event Parser\n57: // ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n58: \n59: export interface ParsedOutput {\n60:   sessionId: string | null;\n61:   completed: boolean;\n62:   errored: boolean;\n63:   lastError: string | null;\n64:   events: OpenCodeEvent[];\n65: }\n66: \n67: export function parseEvents(rawOutput: string): ParsedOutput {\n68:   const result: ParsedOutput = {\n69:     sessionId: null,\n70:     completed: false,\n71:     errored: false,\n72:     lastError: null,\n73:     events: [],\n74:   };\n75: \n76:   const lines = rawOutput.split(\"\\n\").filter((l) => l.trim());\n77: \n78:   for (const line of lines) {\n79:     try {\n80:       const event = JSON.parse(line) as OpenCodeEvent;\n81:       result.events.push(event);\n82: \n83:       if (event.sessionID && !result.sessionId) {\n84:         result.sessionId = event.sessionID;\n85:       }\n86: \n87:       if (\n88:         event.type === \"step_finish\" &&\n89:         event.part?.reason === \"stop\"\n90:       ) {\n91:         result.completed = true;\n92:       }\n93: \n94:       if (\n95:         event.type === \"tool_use\" &&\n96:         event.part?.state?.status === \"error\"\n97:       ) {\n98:         result.errored = true;\n99:         result.lastError = event.part.state.error ?? \"unknown tool error\";\n100:       }\n101:     } catch {\n102:       // Not valid JSON — skip\n103:     }\n104:   }\n105: \n106:   return result;\n107: }\n108: \n109: // ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n110: // Activity Extraction\n111: // ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n112: \n113: function shortPath(fullPath: string | undefined, maxLen: number = 30): string {\n114:   if (!fullPath) return \"\";\n115:   const parts = fullPath.replace(/^\\/+/, \"\").split(\"/\");\n116:   const short =\n117:     parts.length > 1\n118:       ? parts.slice(-2).join(\"/\")\n119:       : parts[parts.length - 1];\n120:   if (short.length <= maxLen) return short;\n121:   const fname = parts[parts.length - 1];\n122:   return fname.length <= maxLen ? fname : fname.slice(0, maxLen - 1) + \"\\u2026\";\n123: }\n124: \n125: function shortCmd(cmd: string | undefined, maxLen: number = 30): string {\n126:   if (!cmd) return \"\";\n127:   const first = cmd.split(\"\\n\")[0].trim();\n128:   if (first.length <= maxLen) return first;\n129:   return first.slice(0, maxLen - 1) + \"\\u2026\";\n130: }\n131: \n132: /**\n133:  * Map an event to a human-readable activity string.\n134:  */\n135: export function extractActivity(event: OpenCodeEvent): string | null {\n136:   switch (event.type) {\n137:     case \"step_start\":\n138:       return \"thinking\\u2026\";\n139: \n140:     case \"tool_use\": {\n141:       const toolName = (event.part?.tool ?? \"\").toLowerCase();\n142:       const input = event.part?.state?.input ?? {};\n143:       const status = event.part?.state?.status ?? \"\";\n144: \n145:       if (status === \"error\") {\n146:         return `${toolName}: error`;\n147:       }\n148: \n149:       switch (toolName) {\n150:         case \"read\":\n151:           return `reading ${shortPath(input.filePath ?? input.path)}`;\n152:         case \"write\":\n153:           return `writing ${shortPath(input.filePath ?? input.path)}`;\n154:         case \"edit\":\n155:           return `editing ${shortPath(input.filePath ?? input.path)}`;\n156:         case \"bash\":\n157:         case \"command\":\n158:         case \"terminal\": {\n159:           const cmd = input.command ?? input.cmd ?? \"\";\n160:           // Detect HITL ask script invocation\n161:           if (cmd.includes(\"hitl-ask\")) {\n162:             return \"waiting for human…\";\n163:           }\n164:           return `$ ${shortCmd(cmd)}`;\n165:         }\n166:         case \"glob\":\n167:           return `finding: ${shortPath(input.pattern)}`;\n168:         case \"grep\":\n169:         case \"search\":\n170:           return `searching: ${(input.pattern ?? \"\").slice(0, 25)}`;\n171:         case \"task\":\n172:           return \"delegating task\\u2026\";\n173:         case \"webfetch\":\n174:         case \"web_fetch\":\n175:           return \"fetching URL\\u2026\";\n176:         case \"todowrite\":\n177:         case \"todo_write\":\n178:           return \"planning\\u2026\";\n179:         case \"question\":\n180:           return \"asking question\\u2026\";\n181:         case \"jcodemunch_index_folder\":\n182:         case \"jcodemunch_index_repo\":\n183:           return \"indexing code\\u2026\";\n184:         case \"jcodemunch_search_symbols\":\n185:         case \"jcodemunch_search_text\":\n186:           return \"searching symbols\\u2026\";\n187:         case \"jcodemunch_get_file_outline\":\n188:           return `outlining ${shortPath(input.file_path)}`;\n189:         case \"jcodemunch_get_symbol\":\n190:         case \"jcodemunch_get_symbols\":\n191:           return \"reading symbol\\u2026\";\n192:         default:\n193:           return `tool: ${toolName}`;\n194:       }\n195:     }\n196: \n197:     case \"text\":\n198:       return \"responding\\u2026\";\n199: \n200:     case \"step_finish\":\n201:       if (event.part?.reason === \"stop\") return \"done\";\n202:       if (event.part?.reason === \"tool-calls\") return null;\n203:       return null;\n204: \n205:     default:\n206:       return null;\n207:   }\n208: }\n209: \n210: /**\n211:  * Format an event into a human-readable log line for the activity stream.\n212:  */\n213: export function formatEventForLog(event: OpenCodeEvent): string | null {\n214:   switch (event.type) {\n215:     case \"step_start\":\n216:       return \"-- step started\";\n217: \n218:     case \"tool_use\": {\n219:       const toolName = event.part?.tool ?? \"unknown\";\n220:       const input = event.part?.state?.input ?? {};\n221:       const status = event.part?.state?.status ?? \"\";\n222:       const output = event.part?.state?.output ?? \"\";\n223:       const error = event.part?.state?.error ?? \"\";\n224: \n225:       let line = `>> ${toolName}`;\n226:       switch (toolName.toLowerCase()) {\n227:         case \"read\":\n228:           line = `>> read ${shortPath(input.filePath ?? input.path, 50)}`;\n229:           break;\n230:         case \"write\":\n231:           line = `>> write ${shortPath(input.filePath ?? input.path, 50)}`;\n232:           break;\n233:         case \"edit\":\n234:           line = `>> edit ${shortPath(input.filePath ?? input.path, 50)}`;\n235:           break;\n236:         case \"bash\":\n237:         case \"command\":\n238:           line = `>> $ ${shortCmd(input.command ?? input.cmd, 60)}`;\n239:           break;\n240:         case \"glob\":\n241:           line = `>> glob ${input.pattern ?? \"\"}`;\n242:           break;\n243:         case \"grep\":\n244:           line = `>> grep \"${(input.pattern ?? \"\").slice(0, 30)}\"`;\n245:           break;\n246:         case \"task\":\n247:           line = `>> task: ${(input.description ?? input.prompt ?? \"\").slice(0, 50)}`;\n248:           break;\n249:       }\n250: \n251:       if (status === \"completed\" && output) {\n252:         const preview = output.split(\"\\n\")[0].slice(0, 80);\n253:         return `${line}\\n   ${preview}${output.length > 80 ? \"\\u2026\" : \"\"}`;\n254:       }\n255:       if (status === \"error\" && error) {\n256:         return `${line}\\n!! ${error.slice(0, 100)}`;\n257:       }\n258:       return line;\n259:     }\n260: \n261:     case \"text\": {\n262:       const text = event.part?.text ?? \"\";\n263:       if (!text.trim()) return null;\n264:       const firstLine = text.split(\"\\n\").find((l: string) => l.trim())?.trim() ?? \"\";\n265:       if (firstLine.length === 0) return null;\n266:       return `   ${firstLine.slice(0, 120)}${firstLine.length > 120 ? \"\\u2026\" : \"\"}`;\n267:     }\n268: \n269:     case \"step_finish\": {\n270:       const reason = event.part?.reason ?? \"\";\n271:       const tokens = event.part?.tokens;\n272:       if (reason === \"stop\") {\n273:         const tokStr = tokens\n274:           ? ` (${tokens.input}in/${tokens.output}out)`\n275:           : \"\";\n276:         return `-- done${tokStr}`;\n277:       }\n278:       return null;\n279:     }\n280: \n281:     default:\n282:       return null;\n283:   }\n284: }\n285: \n286: // ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n287: // Per-agent Activity Log (in-memory ring buffer for TUI)\n288: // ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n289: \n290: export interface ActivityEntry {\n291:   timestamp: string;\n292:   text: string;\n293: }\n294: \n295: const MAX_ACTIVITY_LINES = 500;\n296: \n297: // ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n298: // Process Monitor\n299: // ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n300: \n301: export interface MonitorCallbacks {\n302:   onSessionId?: (featureId: string, sessionId: string) => void;\n303:   onComplete?: (featureId: string) => void;\n304:   onError?: (featureId: string, error: string) => void;\n305:   onOutput?: (featureId: string, data: string) => void;\n306:   onActivity?: (featureId: string, activity: string) => void;\n307:   /** Called when an agent asks a human question via HITL */\n308:   onQuestion?: (featureId: string, questionText: string) => void;\n309: }\n310: \n311: interface MonitoredProcess {\n312:   featureId: string;\n313:   process: ChildProcess;\n314:   stdout: string;\n315:   stderr: string;\n316:   sessionId: string | null;\n317:   done: boolean;\n318:   lineBuffer: string;\n319:   sawFinalStop: boolean;\n320: }\n321: \n322: /**\n323:  * Monitor a set of headless agent processes.\n324:  * Collects stdout, parses events, and calls callbacks on state changes.\n325:  */\n326: export class ProcessMonitor {\n327:   private processes: Map<string, MonitoredProcess> = new Map();\n328:   private callbacks: MonitorCallbacks;\n329:   private logDir: string;\n330:   /** Per-agent activity log for TUI preview pane */\n331:   public activityLogs: Map<string, ActivityEntry[]> = new Map();\n332: \n333:   constructor(projectRoot: string, callbacks: MonitorCallbacks = {}) {\n334:     this.callbacks = callbacks;\n335:     this.logDir = resolve(projectRoot, LOG_DIR_NAME);\n336:     if (!existsSync(this.logDir)) {\n337:       mkdirSync(this.logDir, { recursive: true });\n338:     }\n339:   }\n340: \n341:   private pushActivity(featureId: string, text: string): void {\n342:     if (!this.activityLogs.has(featureId)) {\n343:       this.activityLogs.set(featureId, []);\n344:     }\n345:     const log = this.activityLogs.get(featureId)!;\n346:     for (const line of text.split(\"\\n\")) {\n347:       log.push({ timestamp: new Date().toISOString().slice(11, 19), text: line });\n348:     }\n349:     if (log.length > MAX_ACTIVITY_LINES) {\n350:       log.splice(0, log.length - MAX_ACTIVITY_LINES);\n351:     }\n352:   }\n353: \n354:   private writeLog(featureId: string, data: string): void {\n355:     try {\n356:       const logFile = resolve(this.logDir, `${featureId}.log`);\n357:       appendFileSync(logFile, data);\n358:     } catch {\n359:       // Non-critical\n360:     }\n361:   }\n362: \n363:   getActivityLog(featureId: string): ActivityEntry[] {\n364:     return this.activityLogs.get(featureId) ?? [];\n365:   }\n366: \n367:   addProcess(featureId: string, child: ChildProcess): void {\n368:     const monitored: MonitoredProcess = {\n369:       featureId,\n370:       process: child,\n371:       stdout: \"\",\n372:       stderr: \"\",\n373:       sessionId: null,\n374:       done: false,\n375:       lineBuffer: \"\",\n376:       sawFinalStop: false,\n377:     };\n378: \n379:     this.pushActivity(featureId, \"-- agent process started\");\n380:     this.writeLog(featureId, `[wombo] Process started at ${new Date().toISOString()}\\n`);\n381: \n382:     child.stdout?.on(\"data\", (data: Buffer) => {\n383:       const chunk = data.toString();\n384:       monitored.stdout += chunk;\n385:       this.callbacks.onOutput?.(featureId, chunk);\n386:       this.writeLog(featureId, chunk);\n387: \n388:       monitored.lineBuffer += chunk;\n389:       const lines = monitored.lineBuffer.split(\"\\n\");\n390:       monitored.lineBuffer = lines.pop() ?? \"\";\n391: \n392:       for (const line of lines) {\n393:         const trimmed = line.trim();\n394:         if (!trimmed) continue;\n395:         try {\n396:           const event = JSON.parse(trimmed) as OpenCodeEvent;\n397: \n398:           if (!monitored.sessionId && event.sessionID) {\n399:             monitored.sessionId = event.sessionID;\n400:             this.callbacks.onSessionId?.(featureId, event.sessionID);\n401:             this.pushActivity(featureId, `-- session: ${event.sessionID}`);\n402:           }\n403: \n404:           const activity = extractActivity(event);\n405:           if (activity) {\n406:             this.callbacks.onActivity?.(featureId, activity);\n407:           }\n408: \n409:           const logLine = formatEventForLog(event);\n410:           if (logLine) {\n411:             this.pushActivity(featureId, logLine);\n412:           }\n413: \n414:           if (\n415:             event.type === \"step_finish\" &&\n416:             event.part?.reason === \"stop\"\n417:           ) {\n418:             monitored.sawFinalStop = true;\n419:           }\n420:         } catch {\n421:           if (trimmed.length > 0 && trimmed.length < 500) {\n422:             this.pushActivity(featureId, `[raw] ${trimmed.slice(0, 120)}`);\n423:           }\n424:         }\n425:       }\n426:     });\n427: \n428:     child.stderr?.on(\"data\", (data: Buffer) => {\n429:       const chunk = data.toString();\n430:       monitored.stderr += chunk;\n431:       this.writeLog(featureId, `[stderr] ${chunk}`);\n432:       const lines = chunk.split(\"\\n\").filter((l) => l.trim());\n433:       for (const line of lines) {\n434:         this.pushActivity(featureId, `[stderr] ${line.trim().slice(0, 120)}`);\n435:       }\n436:     });\n437: \n438:     child.on(\"exit\", (code) => {\n439:       monitored.done = true;\n440:       this.pushActivity(featureId, `-- process exited (code ${code})`);\n441:       this.writeLog(featureId, `\\n[wombo] Process exited with code ${code} at ${new Date().toISOString()}\\n`);\n442: \n443:       if (code === 0 || monitored.sawFinalStop) {\n444:         this.callbacks.onComplete?.(featureId);\n445:       } else {\n446:         const error =\n447:           monitored.stderr.slice(-2000) ||\n448:           `Process exited with code ${code}`;\n449:         this.callbacks.onError?.(featureId, error);\n450:       }\n451:     });\n452: \n453:     child.on(\"error\", (err) => {\n454:       monitored.done = true;\n455:       this.pushActivity(featureId, `!! process error: ${err.message}`);\n456:       this.writeLog(featureId, `\\n[wombo] Process error: ${err.message}\\n`);\n457:       this.callbacks.onError?.(featureId, err.message);\n458:     });\n459: \n460:     this.processes.set(featureId, monitored);\n461:   }\n462: \n463:   getSessionId(featureId: string): string | null {\n464:     return this.processes.get(featureId)?.sessionId ?? null;\n465:   }\n466: \n467:   getOutput(featureId: string): string {\n468:     return this.processes.get(featureId)?.stdout ?? \"\";\n469:   }\n470: \n471:   isRunning(featureId: string): boolean {\n472:     const m = this.processes.get(featureId);\n473:     if (!m) return false;\n474:     if (m.done) return false;\n475:     return isProcessRunning(m.process.pid!);\n476:   }\n477: \n478:   allDone(): boolean {\n479:     for (const m of this.processes.values()) {\n480:       if (!m.done) return false;\n481:     }\n482:     return true;\n483:   }\n484: \n485:   activeCount(): number {\n486:     let count = 0;\n487:     for (const m of this.processes.values()) {\n488:       if (!m.done) count++;\n489:     }\n490:     return count;\n491:   }\n492: \n493:   remove(featureId: string): void {\n494:     const m = this.processes.get(featureId);\n495:     if (m && !m.done) {\n496:       try {\n497:         m.process.kill(\"SIGTERM\");\n498:       } catch {}\n499:     }\n500:     this.processes.delete(featureId);\n501:   }\n502: \n503:   killAll(): void {\n504:     for (const id of this.processes.keys()) {\n505:       this.remove(id);\n506:     }\n507:   }\n508: \n509:   waitAll(pollIntervalMs: number = 1000): Promise<void> {\n510:     return new Promise((resolve) => {\n511:       const check = () => {\n512:         if (this.allDone()) {\n513:           resolve();\n514:         } else {\n515:           setTimeout(check, pollIntervalMs);\n516:         }\n517:       };\n518:       check();\n519:     });\n520:   }\n521: }\n\n(End of file - total 521 lines)\n</content>","title":"src/lib/monitor.ts","metadata":{"preview":"/**\n * monitor.ts — Parse JSON events from agent and detect completion/failure.\n *\n * Responsibilities:\n *   - Parse newline-delimited JSON events from agent stdout\n *   - Detect session completion (agent finished)\n *   - Detect session ID from events\n *   - Detect errors and failures\n *   - Write per-agent raw log files for diagnostics\n *   - Maintain per-agent parsed activity log for TUI preview\n */\n\nimport type { ChildProcess } from \"node:child_process\";\nimport { isProcessRunning } from \"./launcher.js\";\nimport { mkdirSync, appendFileSync, existsSync } from \"node:fs\";\nimport { resolve } from \"node:path\";\n\n// ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n// Log directory name (configurable would be overkill here)\n// ---------------------------------------------------------------------------","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"time":{"start":1773481722744,"end":1773481722748}}}}
{"type":"text","timestamp":1773481723285,"sessionID":"ses_3144093abffe4EFLXWMouX7qVB","part":{"id":"prt_cebbf78d0001FxwBqe5KN6BVsD","sessionID":"ses_3144093abffe4EFLXWMouX7qVB","messageID":"msg_cebbf6c93001XBFnCRrG1MYmTc","type":"text","text":"\n\nI'll start by reading the AGENTS.md file and exploring the codebase to understand the architecture before diving into the audit.","time":{"start":1773481723284,"end":1773481723284}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1773481723291,"sessionID":"ses_3144093abffe4EFLXWMouX7qVB","part":{"id":"prt_cebbf8379001IsQhN3MQdH7eX7","sessionID":"ses_3144093abffe4EFLXWMouX7qVB","messageID":"msg_cebbf6c93001XBFnCRrG1MYmTc","type":"tool","callID":"toolu_vrtx_01GWAdmPVQ5t2U1u9iaPmcU7","tool":"read","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/fulgidus/Documents/wombo-combo-worktrees/wave-detach-audit/src/lib/tui.ts"},"output":"<path>/home/fulgidus/Documents/wombo-combo-worktrees/wave-detach-audit/src/lib/tui.ts</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>1: /**\n2:  * tui.ts — Blessed-based TUI dashboard for wombo-combo.\n3:  *\n4:  * Layout:\n5:  *   ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n6:  *   │ Header: Wave ID, base branch, mode, model   │\n7:  *   ├──────────────────────────┬──────────────────┤\n8:  *   │ Agent Table              │ Preview Pane     │\n9:  *   │ (selectable rows with    │ (parsed activity │\n10:  *   │  status, activity,       │  stream for the  │\n11:  *   │  progress bars, elapsed) │  selected agent) │\n12:  *   ├──────────────────────────┴──────────────────┤\n13:  *   │ Status bar: keybinds + summary counts       │\n14:  *   └─────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n15:  *\n16:  * Keybinds:\n17:  *   Up/Down   — navigate agent list\n18:  *   Enter     — attach to selected agent's multiplexer session (interactive mode)\n19:  *   r         — retry a failed/stuck agent\n20:  *   b         — show build log for selected agent\n21:  *   p         — toggle auto-scroll (pause/resume)\n22:  *   q / C-c   — quit\n23:  */\n24: \n25: import blessed from \"neo-blessed\";\n26: import type { Widgets } from \"neo-blessed\";\n27: import type { WaveState, AgentState, AgentStatus } from \"./state.js\";\n28: import { agentCounts } from \"./state.js\";\n29: import type { ProcessMonitor, ActivityEntry } from \"./monitor.js\";\n30: import { execSync } from \"node:child_process\";\n31: import { readFileSync } from \"node:fs\";\n32: import { resolve } from \"node:path\";\n33: import type { WomboConfig } from \"../config.js\";\n34: import {\n35:   detectMultiplexer,\n36:   muxHasSession,\n37:   muxAttach,\n38:   muxDisplayName,\n39: } from \"./multiplexer.js\";\n40: import { QuestionPopup } from \"./tui-question-popup.js\";\n41: import type { HitlQuestion } from \"./hitl-channel.js\";\n42: \n43: // ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n44: // Types\n45: // ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n46: \n47: export interface TUIOptions {\n48:   state: WaveState;\n49:   monitor: ProcessMonitor;\n50:   onQuit: () => void;\n51:   /** Whether the wave is running in interactive (multiplexer) mode. */\n52:   interactive?: boolean;\n53:   /** Project root path (for locating log files). */\n54:   projectRoot: string;\n55:   /** Config (for multiplexer session prefix, log dir, etc.) */\n56:   config: WomboConfig;\n57:   /** Callback to retry a failed/stuck agent from the TUI. */\n58:   onRetry?: (featureId: string) => void;\n59:   /** Callback when the user answers an HITL question. */\n60:   onAnswer?: (agentId: string, questionId: string, answerText: string) => void;\n61: }\n62: \n63: // ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n64: // Color Map\n65: // ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n66: \n67: const STATUS_COLORS: Record<AgentStatus, string> = {\n68:   queued: \"gray\",\n69:   installing: \"cyan\",\n70:   running: \"blue\",\n71:   completed: \"yellow\",\n72:   verified: \"green\",\n73:   failed: \"red\",\n74:   merged: \"magenta\",\n75:   retry: \"yellow\",\n76:   resolving_conflict: \"cyan\",\n77: };\n78: \n79: const STATUS_ICONS: Record<AgentStatus, string> = {\n80:   queued: \"·\",\n81:   installing: \"⟳\",\n82:   running: \"●\",\n83:   completed: \"○\",\n84:   verified: \"✓\",\n85:   failed: \"✗\",\n86:   merged: \"◆\",\n87:   retry: \"↻\",\n88:   resolving_conflict: \"⚡\",\n89: };\n90: \n91: // ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n92: // Helpers\n93: // ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n94: \n95: /**\n96:  * Escape curly braces so blessed doesn't interpret them as formatting tags.\n97:  * Blessed uses {color-fg}...{/color-fg} syntax; unmatched or malformed braces\n98:  * in user-provided text (JSON, Python dicts, shell commands, etc.) crash the\n99:  * renderer. We replace { and } with the Unicode fullwidth equivalents which\n100:  * render visually similar but are not parsed by blessed.\n101:  */\n102: function escapeBlessedTags(text: string): string {\n103:   return text.replace(/\\{/g, \"｛\").replace(/\\}/g, \"｝\");\n104: }\n105: \n106: function elapsed(startedAt: string | null): string {\n107:   if (!startedAt) return \"-\";\n108:   const start = new Date(startedAt).getTime();\n109:   const diffMs = Date.now() - start;\n110:   const secs = Math.floor(diffMs / 1000);\n111:   if (secs < 60) return `${secs}s`;\n112:   const mins = Math.floor(secs / 60);\n113:   if (mins < 60) return `${mins}m`;\n114:   const hours = Math.floor(mins / 60);\n115:   return `${hours}h${mins % 60}m`;\n116: }\n117: \n118: function progressBar(\n119:   elapsedMs: number,\n120:   estimateMs: number,\n121:   width: number = 10\n122: ): string {\n123:   if (estimateMs <= 0) return \"░\".repeat(width);\n124:   const ratio = Math.min(elapsedMs / estimateMs, 1);\n125:   const filled = Math.round(ratio * width);\n126:   return \"█\".repeat(filled) + \"░\".repeat(width - filled);\n127: }\n128: \n129: // ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n130: // TUI Dashboard Class\n131: // ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n132: \n133: export class WomboTUI {\n134:   private screen: Widgets.Screen;\n135:   private headerBox: Widgets.BoxElement;\n136:   private agentList: Widgets.ListElement;\n137:   private previewBox: Widgets.Log;\n138:   private statusBar: Widgets.BoxElement;\n139:   private buildLogBox: Widgets.Log;\n140: \n141:   private state: WaveState;\n142:   private monitor: ProcessMonitor;\n143:   private onQuit: () => void;\n144:   private onRetry?: (featureId: string) => void;\n145:   private onAnswer?: (agentId: string, questionId: string, answerText: string) => void;\n146:   private interactive: boolean;\n147:   private projectRoot: string;\n148:   private config: WomboConfig;\n149: \n150:   private selectedIndex: number = 0;\n151:   private autoScroll: boolean = true;\n152:   private showingBuildLog: boolean = false;\n153:   private showingLogFile: boolean = false;\n154:   private logFileBox: Widgets.Log | null = null;\n155:   private refreshTimer: ReturnType<typeof setInterval> | null = null;\n156:   private waveComplete: boolean = false;\n157:   private waveCompleteResolve: (() => void) | null = null;\n158: \n159:   /** Pending HITL questions from agents */\n160:   private pendingQuestions: HitlQuestion[] = [];\n161:   /** Active question popup (null when closed) */\n162:   private questionPopup: QuestionPopup | null = null;\n163: \n164:   /** Saved originals for console interception */\n165:   private origConsoleLog: typeof console.log = console.log;\n166:   private origConsoleError: typeof console.error = console.error;\n167:   private origConsoleWarn: typeof console.warn = console.warn;\n168:   /** System messages captured while TUI is active */\n169:   private systemMessages: ActivityEntry[] = [];\n170: \n171:   constructor(opts: TUIOptions) {\n172:     this.state = opts.state;\n173:     this.monitor = opts.monitor;\n174:     this.onQuit = opts.onQuit;\n175:     this.onRetry = opts.onRetry;\n176:     this.onAnswer = opts.onAnswer;\n177:     this.interactive = opts.interactive ?? false;\n178:     this.projectRoot = opts.projectRoot;\n179:     this.config = opts.config;\n180: \n181:     // Create screen\n182:     this.screen = blessed.screen({\n183:       smartCSR: true,\n184:       title: `wombo-combo — ${opts.state.wave_id}`,\n185:       fullUnicode: true,\n186:     });\n187: \n188:     // Header\n189:     this.headerBox = blessed.box({\n190:       top: 0,\n191:       left: 0,\n192:       width: \"100%\",\n193:       height: 3,\n194:       tags: true,\n195:       style: {\n196:         fg: \"white\",\n197:         bg: \"black\",\n198:       },\n199:     });\n200: \n201:     // Agent list (left pane)\n202:     this.agentList = blessed.list({\n203:       top: 3,\n204:       left: 0,\n205:       width: \"55%\",\n206:       height: \"100%-6\",\n207:       tags: true,\n208:       scrollable: true,\n209:       mouse: true,\n210:       keys: true,\n211:       vi: true,\n212:       border: {\n213:         type: \"line\",\n214:       },\n215:       style: {\n216:         border: { fg: \"gray\" },\n217:         selected: {\n218:           bg: \"blue\",\n219:           fg: \"white\",\n220:           bold: true,\n221:         },\n222:         item: {\n223:           fg: \"white\",\n224:         },\n225:       },\n226:       label: \" Agents \",\n227:     });\n228: \n229:     // Preview pane (right pane)\n230:     this.previewBox = blessed.log({\n231:       top: 3,\n232:       left: \"55%\",\n233:       width: \"45%\",\n234:       height: \"100%-6\",\n235:       tags: true,\n236:       scrollable: true,\n237:       mouse: true,\n238:       keys: false,\n239:       scrollbar: {\n240:         ch: \"│\",\n241:         style: { fg: \"cyan\" },\n242:       },\n243:       border: {\n244:         type: \"line\",\n245:       },\n246:       style: {\n247:         border: { fg: \"gray\" },\n248:         fg: \"white\",\n249:       },\n250:       label: \" Activity \",\n251:     });\n252: \n253:     // Build log overlay (hidden by default)\n254:     this.buildLogBox = blessed.log({\n255:       top: 3,\n256:       left: \"10%\",\n257:       width: \"80%\",\n258:       height: \"100%-6\",\n259:       tags: true,\n260:       scrollable: true,\n261:       mouse: true,\n262:       keys: true,\n263:       scrollbar: {\n264:         ch: \"│\",\n265:         style: { fg: \"yellow\" },\n266:       },\n267:       border: {\n268:         type: \"line\",\n269:       },\n270:       style: {\n271:         border: { fg: \"yellow\" },\n272:         fg: \"white\",\n273:       },\n274:       label: \" Build Log \",\n275:       hidden: true,\n276:     });\n277: \n278:     // Status bar\n279:     this.statusBar = blessed.box({\n280:       bottom: 0,\n281:       left: 0,\n282:       width: \"100%\",\n283:       height: 3,\n284:       tags: true,\n285:       style: {\n286:         fg: \"white\",\n287:         bg: \"black\",\n288:       },\n289:     });\n290: \n291:     // Assemble\n292:     this.screen.append(this.headerBox);\n293:     this.screen.append(this.agentList);\n294:     this.screen.append(this.previewBox);\n295:     this.screen.append(this.buildLogBox);\n296:     this.screen.append(this.statusBar);\n297: \n298:     // Focus the agent list\n299:     this.agentList.focus();\n300: \n301:     // Bind keys\n302:     this.bindKeys();\n303:   }\n304: \n305:   // -------------------------------------------------------------------------\n306:   // Key Bindings\n307:   // -------------------------------------------------------------------------\n308: \n309:   private bindKeys(): void {\n310:     // Quit\n311:     this.screen.key([\"q\", \"C-c\"], () => {\n312:       this.stop();\n313:       if (this.waveComplete && this.waveCompleteResolve) {\n314:         // Wave is done — just close TUI and resolve the wait promise\n315:         this.waveCompleteResolve();\n316:       } else {\n317:         // Wave still running — trigger the abort/interrupt handler\n318:         this.onQuit();\n319:       }\n320:     });\n321: \n322:     // Navigate agent list\n323:     this.agentList.on(\"select item\", (_item: any, index: number) => {\n324:       this.selectedIndex = index;\n325:       this.refreshPreview();\n326:     });\n327: \n328:     // Enter — multiplexer attach\n329:     this.screen.key([\"enter\"], () => {\n330:       this.muxAttach();\n331:     });\n332: \n333:     // b — toggle build log\n334:     this.screen.key([\"b\"], () => {\n335:       this.toggleBuildLog();\n336:     });\n337: \n338:     // p — toggle auto-scroll\n339:     this.screen.key([\"p\"], () => {\n340:       this.autoScroll = !this.autoScroll;\n341:       this.refreshStatusBar();\n342:     });\n343: \n344:     // r — retry failed/stuck agent\n345:     this.screen.key([\"r\"], () => {\n346:       this.retrySelected();\n347:     });\n348: \n349:     // h — open HITL question popup\n350:     this.screen.key([\"h\"], () => {\n351:       this.openQuestionPopup();\n352:     });\n353: \n354:     // Escape — close build log, log file overlay, or question popup\n355:     this.screen.key([\"escape\"], () => {\n356:       if (this.questionPopup && !this.questionPopup.isDestroyed()) {\n357:         this.questionPopup.close();\n358:         this.questionPopup = null;\n359:         this.agentList.focus();\n360:         this.screen.render();\n361:       } else if (this.showingBuildLog) {\n362:         this.showingBuildLog = false;\n363:         this.buildLogBox.hide();\n364:         this.agentList.focus();\n365:         this.screen.render();\n366:       } else if (this.showingLogFile && this.logFileBox) {\n367:         this.showingLogFile = false;\n368:         this.logFileBox.destroy();\n369:         this.logFileBox = null;\n370:         this.agentList.focus();\n371:         this.screen.render();\n372:       }\n373:     });\n374:   }\n375: \n376:   // -------------------------------------------------------------------------\n377:   // Start / Stop\n378:   // -------------------------------------------------------------------------\n379: \n380:   start(): void {\n381:     this.interceptConsole();\n382:     this.refresh();\n383:     this.screen.render();\n384: \n385:     // Auto-refresh every 2 seconds\n386:     this.refreshTimer = setInterval(() => {\n387:       this.refresh();\n388:     }, 2000);\n389:   }\n390: \n391:   stop(): void {\n392:     this.restoreConsole();\n393:     if (this.refreshTimer) {\n394:       clearInterval(this.refreshTimer);\n395:       this.refreshTimer = null;\n396:     }\n397:     this.screen.destroy();\n398:   }\n399: \n400:   /**\n401:    * Intercept console.log/error/warn so they don't corrupt the TUI.\n402:    * Messages are captured into systemMessages and shown in the preview\n403:    * when no specific agent is producing activity.\n404:    */\n405:   private interceptConsole(): void {\n406:     this.origConsoleLog = console.log;\n407:     this.origConsoleError = console.error;\n408:     this.origConsoleWarn = console.warn;\n409: \n410:     const capture = (...args: any[]) => {\n411:       const text = args\n412:         .map((a) => (typeof a === \"string\" ? a : JSON.stringify(a)))\n413:         .join(\" \");\n414:       // Strip ANSI codes for clean TUI display\n415:       const clean = text.replace(/\\x1b\\[[0-9;]*m/g, \"\");\n416:       if (!clean.trim()) return;\n417:       this.systemMessages.push({\n418:         timestamp: new Date().toISOString().slice(11, 19),\n419:         text: clean,\n420:       });\n421:       // Keep bounded\n422:       if (this.systemMessages.length > 200) {\n423:         this.systemMessages.splice(0, this.systemMessages.length - 200);\n424:       }\n425:     };\n426: \n427:     console.log = capture;\n428:     console.error = capture;\n429:     console.warn = capture;\n430:   }\n431: \n432:   /**\n433:    * Restore original console methods.\n434:    */\n435:   private restoreConsole(): void {\n436:     console.log = this.origConsoleLog;\n437:     console.error = this.origConsoleError;\n438:     console.warn = this.origConsoleWarn;\n439:   }\n440: \n441:   /**\n442:    * Update the state reference (called from the monitoring loop).\n443:    */\n444:   updateState(state: WaveState): void {\n445:     this.state = state;\n446:   }\n447: \n448:   /**\n449:    * Mark the wave as complete. The TUI stays open so the user can browse\n450:    * agent logs, build output, etc. The header shows a WAVE COMPLETE banner\n451:    * and the status bar tells the user to press q to exit.\n452:    */\n453:   markWaveComplete(): void {\n454:     this.waveComplete = true;\n455:     this.refresh();\n456:   }\n457: \n458:   /**\n459:    * Returns a Promise that resolves when the user presses q to quit.\n460:    * Used after wave completion so the TUI stays open for post-mortem browsing.\n461:    */\n462:   waitForQuit(): Promise<void> {\n463:     return new Promise<void>((resolve) => {\n464:       this.waveCompleteResolve = resolve;\n465:     });\n466:   }\n467: \n468:   /**\n469:    * Update pending HITL questions. Called from the monitoring loop.\n470:    * If the question popup is open, it gets live-updated too.\n471:    */\n472:   setPendingQuestions(questions: HitlQuestion[]): void {\n473:     this.pendingQuestions = questions;\n474:     if (this.questionPopup && !this.questionPopup.isDestroyed()) {\n475:       this.questionPopup.updateQuestions(questions);\n476:     }\n477:     // Status bar will pick up the badge on next refresh cycle\n478:   }\n479: \n480:   /**\n481:    * Open the HITL question popup modal.\n482:    */\n483:   private openQuestionPopup(): void {\n484:     // Don't open if already open\n485:     if (this.questionPopup && !this.questionPopup.isDestroyed()) return;\n486: \n487:     // Don't open if there are no pending questions\n488:     if (this.pendingQuestions.length === 0) {\n489:       // Flash a message in the preview\n490:       const agent = this.state.agents[this.selectedIndex];\n491:       if (agent) {\n492:         const logs = this.monitor.activityLogs.get(agent.feature_id);\n493:         if (logs) {\n494:           logs.push({\n495:             timestamp: new Date().toISOString().slice(11, 19),\n496:             text: `-- No pending HITL questions`,\n497:           });\n498:         }\n499:         this.refreshPreview();\n500:         this.screen.render();\n501:       }\n502:       return;\n503:     }\n504: \n505:     this.questionPopup = new QuestionPopup(\n506:       this.screen,\n507:       [...this.pendingQuestions], // copy so popup can mutate internally\n508:       {\n509:         onAnswer: (agentId, questionId, answerText) => {\n510:           // Forward to the external callback (which calls submitAnswer)\n511:           if (this.onAnswer) {\n512:             this.onAnswer(agentId, questionId, answerText);\n513:           }\n514:           // Remove from our pending list\n515:           this.pendingQuestions = this.pendingQuestions.filter(\n516:             (q) => !(q.agentId === agentId && q.id === questionId)\n517:           );\n518:         },\n519:         onClose: () => {\n520:           this.questionPopup = null;\n521:           this.agentList.focus();\n522:           this.refreshStatusBar();\n523:           this.screen.render();\n524:         },\n525:       }\n526:     );\n527:   }\n528: \n529:   // -------------------------------------------------------------------------\n530:   // Refresh Logic\n531:   // -------------------------------------------------------------------------\n532: \n533:   private refresh(): void {\n534:     this.refreshHeader();\n535:     this.refreshAgentList();\n536:     this.refreshPreview();\n537:     this.refreshStatusBar();\n538:     this.screen.render();\n539:   }\n540: \n541:   private refreshHeader(): void {\n542:     const s = this.state;\n543:     const counts = agentCounts(s);\n544:     const total = s.agents.length;\n545:     const done = counts.verified + counts.merged;\n546: \n547:     let line1 = ` {bold}wombo-combo{/bold} {gray-fg}${s.wave_id}{/gray-fg}`;\n548:     if (this.waveComplete) {\n549:       line1 += `  {gray-fg}│{/gray-fg}  {bold}{green-fg}WAVE COMPLETE{/green-fg}{/bold}`;\n550:     }\n551:     line1 += `  {gray-fg}│{/gray-fg}  Base: {cyan-fg}${s.base_branch}{/cyan-fg}`;\n552:     line1 += `  {gray-fg}│{/gray-fg}  Mode: ${s.interactive ? \"{green-fg}interactive{/green-fg}\" : \"{blue-fg}headless{/blue-fg}\"}`;\n553:     if (s.model) {\n554:       line1 += `  {gray-fg}│{/gray-fg}  Model: {yellow-fg}${s.model}{/yellow-fg}`;\n555:     }\n556: \n557:     let line2 = ` Progress: {green-fg}${done}{/green-fg}/{white-fg}${total}{/white-fg}`;\n558:     if (counts.running > 0)\n559:       line2 += `  {blue-fg}${counts.running} running{/blue-fg}`;\n560:     if (counts.failed > 0)\n561:       line2 += `  {red-fg}${counts.failed} failed{/red-fg}`;\n562:     if (counts.queued > 0)\n563:       line2 += `  {gray-fg}${counts.queued} queued{/gray-fg}`;\n564:     if (counts.retry > 0)\n565:       line2 += `  {yellow-fg}${counts.retry} retrying{/yellow-fg}`;\n566:     if (counts.resolving_conflict > 0)\n567:       line2 += `  {cyan-fg}${counts.resolving_conflict} resolving{/cyan-fg}`;\n568: \n569:     this.headerBox.setContent(`${line1}\\n${line2}`);\n570:   }\n571: \n572:   private refreshAgentList(): void {\n573:     const items: string[] = [];\n574: \n575:     for (let i = 0; i < this.state.agents.length; i++) {\n576:       const a = this.state.agents[i];\n577:       const color = STATUS_COLORS[a.status];\n578:       const icon = STATUS_ICONS[a.status];\n579: \n580:       // Feature ID (padded)\n581:       const fid =\n582:         a.feature_id.length > 24\n583:           ? a.feature_id.slice(0, 23) + \"…\"\n584:           : a.feature_id.padEnd(24);\n585: \n586:       // Status\n587:       const st = `{${color}-fg}${icon} ${a.status.padEnd(10)}{/${color}-fg}`;\n588: \n589:       // Progress bar\n590:       let pbar = \"\";\n591:       if ((a.status === \"running\" || a.status === \"resolving_conflict\") && a.started_at) {\n592:         const elapsedMs = Date.now() - new Date(a.started_at).getTime();\n593:         // Use actual effort estimate from feature data, fallback to 1h\n594:         const estimateMs = a.effort_estimate_ms ?? 60 * 60 * 1000;\n595:         pbar = ` {cyan-fg}${progressBar(elapsedMs, estimateMs, 8)}{/cyan-fg}`;\n596:       } else if (a.status === \"verified\" || a.status === \"merged\") {\n597:         pbar = ` {green-fg}${\"█\".repeat(8)}{/green-fg}`;\n598:       } else if (a.status === \"failed\") {\n599:         pbar = ` {red-fg}${\"█\".repeat(8)}{/red-fg}`;\n600:       }\n601: \n602:       // Activity (for running/resolving agents)\n603:       let act = \"\";\n604:       if ((a.status === \"running\" || a.status === \"resolving_conflict\") && a.activity) {\n605:         const rawAct =\n606:           a.activity.length > 25 ? a.activity.slice(0, 24) + \"…\" : a.activity;\n607:         const actText = escapeBlessedTags(rawAct);\n608:         act = ` {cyan-fg}${actText}{/cyan-fg}`;\n609:       } else if (a.status === \"installing\") {\n610:         act = \" {cyan-fg}setting up…{/cyan-fg}\";\n611:       }\n612: \n613:       // Elapsed\n614:       const el = elapsed(a.started_at);\n615: \n616:       // Retries\n617:       const retries =\n618:         a.retries > 0 ? ` {yellow-fg}↻${a.retries}{/yellow-fg}` : \"\";\n619: \n620:       items.push(\n621:         ` ${fid} ${st}${pbar}${act}${retries} {gray-fg}${el}{/gray-fg}`\n622:       );\n623:     }\n624: \n625:     // Preserve selection\n626:     const prevSelected = this.selectedIndex;\n627:     this.agentList.setItems(items as any);\n628:     if (prevSelected < items.length) {\n629:       this.agentList.select(prevSelected);\n630:     }\n631:   }\n632: \n633:   private refreshPreview(): void {\n634:     const agent = this.state.agents[this.selectedIndex];\n635:     if (!agent) {\n636:       this.previewBox.setContent(\"{gray-fg}No agent selected{/gray-fg}\");\n637:       return;\n638:     }\n639: \n640:     // Update label\n641:     this.previewBox.setLabel(` ${agent.feature_id} — Activity `);\n642: \n643:     // Get activity log from monitor\n644:     const log = this.monitor.getActivityLog(agent.feature_id);\n645: \n646:     // Also include system messages (build verification, etc.)\n647:     // that mention this agent's feature_id\n648:     const relevantSys = this.systemMessages.filter((m) =>\n649:       m.text.includes(agent.feature_id)\n650:     );\n651: \n652:     if (log.length === 0 && relevantSys.length === 0) {\n653:       this.previewBox.setContent(\n654:         \"{gray-fg}No activity yet. Waiting for agent output…{/gray-fg}\"\n655:       );\n656:       return;\n657:     }\n658: \n659:     // Format log entries\n660:     const lines: string[] = [];\n661:     for (const entry of log) {\n662:       lines.push(this.formatActivityLine(entry));\n663:     }\n664: \n665:     // Append relevant system messages\n666:     if (relevantSys.length > 0) {\n667:       lines.push(\"\");\n668:       lines.push(\"{yellow-fg}-- system --{/yellow-fg}\");\n669:       for (const entry of relevantSys) {\n670:         const ts = `{gray-fg}${entry.timestamp}{/gray-fg}`;\n671:         lines.push(`${ts} {yellow-fg}${escapeBlessedTags(entry.text)}{/yellow-fg}`);\n672:       }\n673:     }\n674: \n675:     this.previewBox.setContent(lines.join(\"\\n\"));\n676: \n677:     // Auto-scroll to bottom\n678:     if (this.autoScroll) {\n679:       this.previewBox.setScrollPerc(100);\n680:     }\n681:   }\n682: \n683:   private formatActivityLine(entry: ActivityEntry): string {\n684:     const ts = `{gray-fg}${entry.timestamp}{/gray-fg}`;\n685:     let text = escapeBlessedTags(entry.text);\n686: \n687:     // Color-code different line types\n688:     if (text.startsWith(\">>\")) {\n689:       text = `{cyan-fg}${text}{/cyan-fg}`;\n690:     } else if (text.startsWith(\"!!\")) {\n691:       text = `{red-fg}${text}{/red-fg}`;\n692:     } else if (text.startsWith(\"--\")) {\n693:       text = `{green-fg}${text}{/green-fg}`;\n694:     } else if (text.startsWith(\"[stderr]\")) {\n695:       text = `{red-fg}${text}{/red-fg}`;\n696:     } else if (text.startsWith(\"[raw]\")) {\n697:       text = `{gray-fg}${text}{/gray-fg}`;\n698:     } else if (text.startsWith(\"   \")) {\n699:       text = `{white-fg}${text}{/white-fg}`;\n700:     }\n701: \n702:     return `${ts} ${text}`;\n703:   }\n704: \n705:   private refreshStatusBar(): void {\n706:     const scrollStatus = this.autoScroll\n707:       ? \"{green-fg}auto-scroll{/green-fg}\"\n708:       : \"{yellow-fg}paused{/yellow-fg}\";\n709: \n710:     const agent = this.state.agents[this.selectedIndex];\n711:     const agentInfo = agent\n712:       ? `{gray-fg}Selected: {white-fg}${agent.feature_id}{/white-fg}{/gray-fg}`\n713:       : \"\";\n714: \n715:     const enterHint = this.interactive\n716:       ? \"{gray-fg}Enter{/gray-fg} attach session\"\n717:       : \"{gray-fg}Enter{/gray-fg} view log\";\n718: \n719:     // HITL badge — show only when there are pending questions\n720:     const hitlBadge =\n721:       this.pendingQuestions.length > 0\n722:         ? `  {bold}{yellow-fg}? ${this.pendingQuestions.length} pending{/yellow-fg}{/bold}  {gray-fg}H{/gray-fg} answer`\n723:         : \"\";\n724: \n725:     let line1: string;\n726:     if (this.waveComplete) {\n727:       line1 = ` {bold}{green-fg}Wave complete.{/green-fg}{/bold}  ${enterHint}  {gray-fg}R{/gray-fg} retry  {gray-fg}B{/gray-fg} build log  {gray-fg}P{/gray-fg} ${scrollStatus}${hitlBadge}  {bold}{yellow-fg}Q{/yellow-fg} exit{/bold}`;\n728:     } else {\n729:       line1 = ` {bold}Keys:{/bold} {gray-fg}\\u2191\\u2193{/gray-fg} navigate  ${enterHint}  {gray-fg}R{/gray-fg} retry  {gray-fg}B{/gray-fg} build log  {gray-fg}P{/gray-fg} ${scrollStatus}${hitlBadge}  {gray-fg}Q{/gray-fg} quit`;\n730:     }\n731:     const line2 = ` ${agentInfo}`;\n732: \n733:     this.statusBar.setContent(`${line1}\\n${line2}`);\n734:   }\n735: \n736:   // -------------------------------------------------------------------------\n737:   // Actions\n738:   // -------------------------------------------------------------------------\n739: \n740:   private muxAttach(): void {\n741:     const agent = this.state.agents[this.selectedIndex];\n742:     if (!agent) return;\n743: \n744:     if (!this.interactive) {\n745:       // Headless mode — show the raw log file in an overlay\n746:       this.showLogFile(agent);\n747:       return;\n748:     }\n749: \n750:     const mux = detectMultiplexer(this.config.agent.multiplexer);\n751:     const sessionName = `${this.config.agent.tmuxPrefix}-${agent.feature_id}`;\n752: \n753:     // Check if multiplexer session exists\n754:     if (!muxHasSession(mux, sessionName)) {\n755:       // No session — show message in preview\n756:       this.monitor.activityLogs.get(agent.feature_id)?.push({\n757:         timestamp: new Date().toISOString().slice(11, 19),\n758:         text: `!! No ${muxDisplayName(mux)} session '${sessionName}' found`,\n759:       });\n760:       this.refreshPreview();\n761:       this.screen.render();\n762:       return;\n763:     }\n764: \n765:     // Detach from blessed, attach to multiplexer session\n766:     this.restoreConsole();\n767:     this.screen.destroy();\n768:     try {\n769:       muxAttach(mux, sessionName);\n770:     } catch {\n771:       // User detached from session — resume TUI\n772:     }\n773: \n774:     // Re-create screen after returning from multiplexer\n775:     this.recreateScreen();\n776:   }\n777: \n778:   /**\n779:    * Retry the selected agent (only if failed or stuck in retry).\n780:    * Resets it to \"queued\" so the polling loop picks it up for a fresh launch.\n781:    */\n782:   private retrySelected(): void {\n783:     const agent = this.state.agents[this.selectedIndex];\n784:     if (!agent) return;\n785: \n786:     const retryableStatuses: AgentStatus[] = [\"failed\", \"retry\"];\n787:     if (!retryableStatuses.includes(agent.status)) {\n788:       // Flash a message in the preview — agent isn't in a retryable state\n789:       const logs = this.monitor.activityLogs.get(agent.feature_id);\n790:       if (logs) {\n791:         logs.push({\n792:           timestamp: new Date().toISOString().slice(11, 19),\n793:           text: `!! Cannot retry — agent status is \"${agent.status}\" (must be failed or retry)`,\n794:         });\n795:       }\n796:       this.refreshPreview();\n797:       this.screen.render();\n798:       return;\n799:     }\n800: \n801:     if (this.onRetry) {\n802:       this.onRetry(agent.feature_id);\n803: \n804:       // Show feedback in preview\n805:       const logs = this.monitor.activityLogs.get(agent.feature_id);\n806:       if (logs) {\n807:         logs.push({\n808:           timestamp: new Date().toISOString().slice(11, 19),\n809:           text: `>> Retry requested — agent will be relaunched`,\n810:         });\n811:       }\n812:       this.refresh();\n813:       this.screen.render();\n814:     }\n815:   }\n816: \n817:   /**\n818:    * Show the raw log file for an agent in an overlay (headless mode).\n819:    */\n820:   private showLogFile(agent: AgentState): void {\n821:     if (this.showingLogFile) {\n822:       // Toggle off\n823:       this.showingLogFile = false;\n824:       if (this.logFileBox) {\n825:         this.logFileBox.destroy();\n826:         this.logFileBox = null;\n827:       }\n828:       this.agentList.focus();\n829:       this.screen.render();\n830:       return;\n831:     }\n832: \n833:     const logPath = resolve(\n834:       this.projectRoot,\n835:       \".wombo-combo\",\n836:       \"logs\",\n837:       `${agent.feature_id}.log`\n838:     );\n839:     let content: string;\n840:     try {\n841:       content = readFileSync(logPath, \"utf-8\");\n842:       if (!content.trim()) {\n843:         content =\n844:           \"{gray-fg}Log file is empty. Agent may not have started producing output yet.{/gray-fg}\";\n845:       }\n846:     } catch {\n847:       content = \"{gray-fg}No log file found at \" + logPath + \"{/gray-fg}\";\n848:     }\n849: \n850:     // Create overlay\n851:     this.logFileBox = blessed.log({\n852:       top: 3,\n853:       left: \"5%\",\n854:       width: \"90%\",\n855:       height: \"100%-6\",\n856:       tags: true,\n857:       scrollable: true,\n858:       mouse: true,\n859:       keys: true,\n860:       scrollbar: {\n861:         ch: \"│\",\n862:         style: { fg: \"cyan\" },\n863:       },\n864:       border: {\n865:         type: \"line\",\n866:       },\n867:       style: {\n868:         border: { fg: \"cyan\" },\n869:         fg: \"white\",\n870:       },\n871:       label: ` Log — ${agent.feature_id} (Esc to close) `,\n872:     });\n873: \n874:     this.screen.append(this.logFileBox);\n875: \n876:     // Truncate to last 200 lines to keep TUI responsive\n877:     const lines = content.split(\"\\n\");\n878:     const truncated =\n879:       lines.length > 200 ? lines.slice(-200).join(\"\\n\") : content;\n880:     this.logFileBox.setContent(escapeBlessedTags(truncated));\n881:     this.logFileBox.setScrollPerc(100);\n882:     this.logFileBox.focus();\n883:     this.showingLogFile = true;\n884:     this.screen.render();\n885:   }\n886: \n887:   private toggleBuildLog(): void {\n888:     const agent = this.state.agents[this.selectedIndex];\n889:     if (!agent) return;\n890: \n891:     if (this.showingBuildLog) {\n892:       this.showingBuildLog = false;\n893:       this.buildLogBox.hide();\n894:       this.agentList.focus();\n895:     } else {\n896:       this.showingBuildLog = true;\n897:       this.buildLogBox.setLabel(` Build Log — ${agent.feature_id} `);\n898: \n899:       if (agent.build_output) {\n900:         this.buildLogBox.setContent(escapeBlessedTags(agent.build_output));\n901:       } else if (agent.build_passed === true) {\n902:         this.buildLogBox.setContent(\n903:           \"{green-fg}Build passed — no errors.{/green-fg}\"\n904:         );\n905:       } else if (agent.build_passed === false) {\n906:         this.buildLogBox.setContent(\n907:           \"{red-fg}Build failed — no output captured.{/red-fg}\"\n908:         );\n909:       } else {\n910:         this.buildLogBox.setContent(\n911:           \"{gray-fg}No build has been run yet.{/gray-fg}\"\n912:         );\n913:       }\n914: \n915:       this.buildLogBox.show();\n916:       this.buildLogBox.focus();\n917:     }\n918:     this.screen.render();\n919:   }\n920: \n921:   /**\n922:    * Re-create the screen after returning from multiplexer attach.\n923:    * Blessed can't resume after destroy, so we rebuild everything.\n924:    */\n925:   private recreateScreen(): void {\n926:     // Re-create screen\n927:     this.screen = blessed.screen({\n928:       smartCSR: true,\n929:       title: `wombo-combo — ${this.state.wave_id}`,\n930:       fullUnicode: true,\n931:     });\n932: \n933:     // Re-create all widgets\n934:     this.headerBox = blessed.box({\n935:       top: 0,\n936:       left: 0,\n937:       width: \"100%\",\n938:       height: 3,\n939:       tags: true,\n940:       style: { fg: \"white\", bg: \"black\" },\n941:     });\n942: \n943:     this.agentList = blessed.list({\n944:       top: 3,\n945:       left: 0,\n946:       width: \"55%\",\n947:       height: \"100%-6\",\n948:       tags: true,\n949:       scrollable: true,\n950:       mouse: true,\n951:       keys: true,\n952:       vi: true,\n953:       border: { type: \"line\" },\n954:       style: {\n955:         border: { fg: \"gray\" },\n956:         selected: { bg: \"blue\", fg: \"white\", bold: true },\n957:         item: { fg: \"white\" },\n958:       },\n959:       label: \" Agents \",\n960:     });\n961: \n962:     this.previewBox = blessed.log({\n963:       top: 3,\n964:       left: \"55%\",\n965:       width: \"45%\",\n966:       height: \"100%-6\",\n967:       tags: true,\n968:       scrollable: true,\n969:       mouse: true,\n970:       keys: false,\n971:       scrollbar: { ch: \"│\", style: { fg: \"cyan\" } },\n972:       border: { type: \"line\" },\n973:       style: { border: { fg: \"gray\" }, fg: \"white\" },\n974:       label: \" Activity \",\n975:     });\n976: \n977:     this.buildLogBox = blessed.log({\n978:       top: 3,\n979:       left: \"10%\",\n980:       width: \"80%\",\n981:       height: \"100%-6\",\n982:       tags: true,\n983:       scrollable: true,\n984:       mouse: true,\n985:       keys: true,\n986:       scrollbar: { ch: \"│\", style: { fg: \"yellow\" } },\n987:       border: { type: \"line\" },\n988:       style: { border: { fg: \"yellow\" }, fg: \"white\" },\n989:       label: \" Build Log \",\n990:       hidden: true,\n991:     });\n992: \n993:     this.statusBar = blessed.box({\n994:       bottom: 0,\n995:       left: 0,\n996:       width: \"100%\",\n997:       height: 3,\n998:       tags: true,\n999:       style: { fg: \"white\", bg: \"black\" },\n1000:     });\n1001: \n1002:     this.screen.append(this.headerBox);\n1003:     this.screen.append(this.agentList);\n1004:     this.screen.append(this.previewBox);\n1005:     this.screen.append(this.buildLogBox);\n1006:     this.screen.append(this.statusBar);\n1007: \n1008:     this.agentList.focus();\n1009:     this.showingBuildLog = false;\n1010:     this.showingLogFile = false;\n1011:     this.logFileBox = null;\n1012:     this.questionPopup = null;\n1013:     this.interceptConsole();\n1014:     this.bindKeys();\n1015:     this.refresh();\n1016:   }\n1017: }\n\n(End of file - total 1017 lines)\n</content>","title":"src/lib/tui.ts","metadata":{"preview":"/**\n * tui.ts — Blessed-based TUI dashboard for wombo-combo.\n *\n * Layout:\n *   ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n *   │ Header: Wave ID, base branch, mode, model   │\n *   ├──────────────────────────┬──────────────────┤\n *   │ Agent Table              │ Preview Pane     │\n *   │ (selectable rows with    │ (parsed activity │\n *   │  status, activity,       │  stream for the  │\n *   │  progress bars, elapsed) │  selected agent) │\n *   ├──────────────────────────┴──────────────────┤\n *   │ Status bar: keybinds + summary counts       │\n *   └─────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n *\n * Keybinds:\n *   Up/Down   — navigate agent list\n *   Enter     — attach to selected agent's multiplexer session (interactive mode)\n *   r         — retry a failed/stuck agent\n *   b         — show build log for selected agent","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"time":{"start":1773481723282,"end":1773481723288}}}}
