{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1773481875539,"sessionID":"ses_3144093abffe4EFLXWMouX7qVB","part":{"id":"prt_cebc1bf2d001gjd1XESQ15qXZ2","sessionID":"ses_3144093abffe4EFLXWMouX7qVB","messageID":"msg_cebc1b50f001lLDUH4agcUwHxu","type":"tool","callID":"toolu_vrtx_01WRKTBz1CjRgMUxLyWNKbRN","tool":"edit","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/fulgidus/Documents/wombo-combo-worktrees/wave-detach-audit/src/commands/launch.ts","newString":"  // Handle graceful shutdown\n  //\n  // Audit (wave-detach-audit): This is the critical shutdown path for headless\n  // agents. Because agents are spawned with `detached: false` (see launcher.ts),\n  // they would be killed by the OS when the parent exits anyway. However, calling\n  // `monitor.killAll()` explicitly before `process.exit(0)` ensures:\n  //   1. Each agent gets SIGTERM (not SIGKILL), allowing graceful shutdown\n  //   2. Wave state is saved BEFORE agents die, preserving progress\n  //   3. The TUI is cleanly destroyed before terminal restoration\n  //\n  // If the parent is killed with SIGKILL (uncatchable), agents die immediately\n  // with no state save. `woco resume` recovers from this by detecting orphaned\n  // worktrees with commits and re-verifying or re-launching as appropriate.\n  process.on(\"SIGINT\", () => {","oldString":"  // Handle graceful shutdown\n  process.on(\"SIGINT\", () => {"},"output":"Edit applied successfully.","title":"src/commands/launch.ts","metadata":{"diagnostics":{"/home/fulgidus/Documents/wombo-combo-worktrees/wave-detach-audit/src/lib/tui.ts":[{"range":{"start":{"line":29,"character":0},"end":{"line":29,"character":46}},"message":"'execSync' is declared but its value is never read.","severity":4,"code":6133,"source":"typescript"}],"/home/fulgidus/Documents/wombo-combo-worktrees/wave-detach-audit/src/lib/launcher.ts":[{"range":{"start":{"line":65,"character":18},"end":{"line":65,"character":25}},"message":"'dirname' is declared but its value is never read.","severity":4,"