{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1773481894778,"sessionID":"ses_3144093abffe4EFLXWMouX7qVB","part":{"id":"prt_cebc209b7001tQxXUrCUHD8b7E","sessionID":"ses_3144093abffe4EFLXWMouX7qVB","messageID":"msg_cebc1fd50001TalYdBKj2YWDlV","type":"tool","callID":"toolu_vrtx_01VPq9rDjZLPueqwdSUWjVnJ","tool":"bash","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"command":"git add src/lib/launcher.ts src/lib/monitor.ts src/lib/tui.ts src/commands/launch.ts && git commit -m \"docs(wave-detach-audit): document agent process lifecycle findings\n\nAudit of the agent process lifecycle when the WomboTUI/monitor is torn down:\n\nKey findings:\n1. Headless agents are spawned with detached:false — they die with the parent.\n   This is INTENTIONAL: stdout must be piped for JSON event parsing.\n2. ProcessMonitor.killAll() sends SIGTERM to each child on shutdown.\n   This is correct: explicit kill ensures state is saved before exit.\n3. TUI screen.destroy() does NOT kill agents — the onQuit callback does.\n   This separation allows TUI recreation after mux attach/detach.\n4. Interactive (mux) agents survive parent death naturally.\n5. Recovery path: woco resume detects orphaned worktrees with commits.\n\nAdded comprehensive lifecycle documentation to:\n- launcher.ts: module-level doc + per-function spawn behavior notes\n- monitor.ts: module-level doc + remove()/killAll() behavior docs\n- tui.ts: start/stop section lifecycle analysis\n- launch.ts: SIGINT handler and onQuit callback audit notes\"","description":"Commit audit documentation"},"output":"[feature/wave-detach-audit 677867e] docs(wave-detach-audit): document agent process lifecycle findings\n 4 files changed, 133 insertions(+), 3 deletions(-)\n","title":"Commit audit documentation","metadata":{"output":"[feature/wave-detach-audit 677867e] docs(wave-detach-audit): document agent process lifecycle findings\n 4 files changed, 133 insertions(+), 3 deletions(-)\n","exit":0,"description":"Commit audit documentation","truncated":false},"time":{"start":1773481894763,"end":1773481894777}}}}
