{"type":"text","timestamp":1773481984925,"sessionID":"ses_3144093abffe4EFLXWMouX7qVB","part":{"id":"prt_cebc35676001oO7NdN4XEp0MII","sessionID":"ses_3144093abffe4EFLXWMouX7qVB","messageID":"msg_cebc34cf2001pVHjnoz50LNWyc","type":"text","text":"The implementation is complete. Here's a summary of what was done:\n\n## Audit Summary\n\n### Findings\n\n1. **Agents are spawned with `detached: false`** — This is **intentional**. Headless agents are child processes tied to the parent. They die when the parent exits. This is required because stdout must be piped for real-time JSON event parsing by ProcessMonitor.\n\n2. **`unref()` is NOT called** — Also intentional. The child process keeps the parent's event loop alive, which is needed for monitoring.\n\n3. **`ProcessMonitor.killAll()` sends SIGTERM** — Called during graceful shutdown (SIGINT, TUI quit). Gives agents a chance for graceful shutdown before state is saved and parent exits.\n\n4. **`TUI.stop()` does NOT kill agents** — Only destroys the blessed screen. Agent killing is done by the `onQuit` callback (configured by launch.ts/resume.ts), which calls `monitor.killAll()`.\n\n5. **Interactive (mux) mode agents survive parent death** — They run in dmux/tmux sessions independent of the parent process.\n\n6. **Recovery path exists** — `woco resume` detects orphaned worktrees with commits and re-verifies or re-launches dead agents.\n\n### Changes Made\n\n- **3 documentation commits**: Added comprehensive lifecycle documentation to `launcher.ts`, `monitor.ts`, `tui.ts`, `launch.ts`, and `resume.ts` explaining the spawn behavior, teardown flow, and recovery mechanisms.\n\n- **1 bugfix commit**: Fixed `resume.ts` `onQuit` callback that only marked `\"running\"` agents as interrupted, missing agents in `\"resolving_conflict\"` status (inconsistency with `launch.ts`).\n\n### What Doesn't Need Changing\n\nThe current architecture is correct for its use case. The `detached: false` + piped stdio design is the right trade-off for reliable monitoring. If agent persistence across parent restarts is needed, the interactive (multiplexer) mode should be used instead.","time":{"start":1773481984924,"end":1773481984924}}}
