{"type":"text","timestamp":1773483414054,"sessionID":"ses_31427856effefwaC38OEq6YCmn","part":{"id":"prt_cebd90f09001pf8d91GfISc4d3","sessionID":"ses_31427856effefwaC38OEq6YCmn","messageID":"msg_cebd906a0001PwKXGWRHiF03jG","type":"text","text":"I've now thoroughly analyzed all the code. Let me summarize the audit findings:\n\n## Audit Findings\n\n### 1. launcher.ts — Are agents spawned with `detached:true` and `unref()`?\n\n**Finding: NO.** All three headless launch functions (`launchHeadless`, `retryHeadless`, `launchConflictResolver`) spawn with:\n- `detached: false` — agents are child processes tied to the parent\n- `unref()` is **NOT** called — children hold the parent's event loop alive\n- `stdio: [\"pipe\", \"pipe\", \"pipe\"]` — stdout/stderr are piped for JSON event parsing\n\n**Consequence**: Agents die when the parent exits. This is **intentional** — the piped stdio streams require the parent to be alive for the ProcessMonitor to parse JSON events.\n\n**Interactive mode** (`launchInteractive`) is different: agents run inside dmux/tmux sessions which are independent of the parent. They survive parent death.\n\n### 2. monitor.ts — Does `ProcessMonitor.stop()`/`killAll()` kill child processes?\n\n**Finding: YES.** `killAll()` iterates all processes and calls `remove()`, which sends SIGTERM to each child. For reconnected processes (PID-only, no ChildProcess handle), `process.kill(pid, 'SIGTERM')` is used directly. However, reconnected processes are intentionally NOT killed (just removed from monitoring).\n\nThere is no `stop()` method on ProcessMonitor — the caller invokes `killAll()` directly.\n\n### 3. tui.ts — Does `screen.destroy()` affect agent processes?\n\n**Finding: NO.** `WomboTUI.stop()` only:\n1. Restores console methods\n2. Clears the refresh timer\n3. Calls `onBeforeDestroy()` callback (flushes state)\n4. Calls `screen.destroy()` (tears down the blessed terminal UI)\n\nAgent termination is handled by the `onQuit` callback, which calls `monitor.killAll()`. The TUI never owns agent processes — it only reads from the monitor.\n\n### Documentation Assessment\n\nI can see that the key files already contain thorough audit documentation:\n- **launcher.ts**: Has a complete module-level JSDoc block (lines 12-45) documenting the agent process lifecycle\n- **monitor.ts**: Has a module-level JSDoc block (lines 12-38) documenting the process lifecycle\n- **tui.ts**: Has inline comments (lines 388-404) documenting the TUI lifecycle\n- **launch.ts**: Has inline audit comments at SIGINT handler and onQuit callback\n- **resume.ts**: Has module-level audit documentation and inline comments\n\nHowever, I notice there's no centralized audit document. The annotations are scattered across files. Let me check if there are any gaps and if the existing annotations need any corrections or improvements.\n\nLet me look at a few more related files to ensure completeness:","time":{"start":1773483414053,"end":1773483414053}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1773483414058,"sessionID":"ses_31427856effefwaC38OEq6YCmn","part":{"id":"prt_cebd94cae001m4tLe0JenbGgJD","sessionID":"ses_31427856effefwaC38OEq6YCmn","messageID":"msg_cebd906a0001PwKXGWRHiF03jG","type":"tool","callID":"toolu_vrtx_01LMsJ49QK8gFHH1UtSDK51C","tool":"read","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/fulgidus/Documents/wombo-combo-worktrees/wave-detach-audit/src/commands/launch.ts","offset":1426},"output":"<path>/home/fulgidus/Documents/wombo-combo-worktrees/wave-detach-audit/src/commands/launch.ts</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>1426:   const { config, model } = opts;\n1427:   const fmt = opts.outputFmt ?? \"text\";\n1428:   const featureMap = new Map(features.map((f) => [f.id, f]));\n1429: \n1430:   // Show dashboard immediately\n1431:   if (fmt === \"text\") printDashboard(state);\n1432: \n1433:   // Launch initial batch — parallelize setup\n1434:   const tolaunch = queuedAgents(state).slice(0, opts.maxConcurrent);\n1435:   if (fmt === \"text\") console.log(`Setting up ${tolaunch.length} agent(s) in parallel...\\n`);\n1436: \n1437:   await Promise.all(\n1438:     tolaunch.map(async (agent) => {\n1439:       updateAgent(state, agent.feature_id, {\n1440:         status: \"installing\",\n1441:         started_at: new Date().toISOString(),\n1442:         activity: \"setting up worktree...\",\n1443:       });\n1444:       saveState(projectRoot, state);\n1445: \n1446:       try {\n1447:         if (worktreeReady(agent.worktree)) {\n1448:           wtLog(agent.feature_id, \"worktree already exists, skipping setup\");\n1449:         } else {\n1450:           await createWorktree(projectRoot, agent.feature_id, state.base_branch, config);\n1451:           updateAgent(state, agent.feature_id, { activity: \"installing deps...\" });\n1452:           await installDeps(agent.worktree, agent.feature_id, config);\n1453:         }\n1454: \n1455:         const prompt = generatePrompt(\n1456:           featureMap.get(agent.feature_id)!,\n1457:           state.base_branch,\n1458:           config,\n1459:           questContext,\n1460:           hitlMode as QuestHitlMode | undefined\n1461:         );\n1462: \n1463:         // Write specialized agent to worktree if applicable\n1464:         const resolution = agentResolutions?.get(agent.feature_id);\n1465:         const agentName = agent.agent_name ?? undefined;\n1466:         if (resolution && isSpecializedAgent(resolution)) {\n1467:           try {\n1468:             const patchedContent = patchImportedAgent(resolution.rawContent, config, projectRoot);\n1469:             writeAgentToWorktree(agent.worktree, resolution.name, patchedContent);\n1470:             wtLog(agent.feature_id, `wrote specialized agent: ${resolution.name}`);\n1471:           } catch (err: any) {\n1472:             wtLog(agent.feature_id, `WARN: failed to write specialized agent, using generalist: ${err.message}`);\n1473:           }\n1474:         }\n1475: \n1476:         wtLog(agent.feature_id, \"launching interactive session...\");\n1477:         const result = launchInteractive({\n1478:           worktreePath: agent.worktree,\n1479:           featureId: agent.feature_id,\n1480:           prompt,\n1481:           model,\n1482:           interactive: true,\n1483:           config,\n1484:           agentName,\n1485:         });\n1486: \n1487:         const muxName = getMultiplexerName(config);\n1488:         updateAgent(state, agent.feature_id, {\n1489:           status: \"running\",\n1490:           pid: result.pid,\n1491:           activity: `${muxName} session active`,\n1492:         });\n1493:         saveState(projectRoot, state);\n1494:         wtLog(agent.feature_id, `${muxName} session: ${config.agent.tmuxPrefix}-${agent.feature_id}`);\n1495:       } catch (err: any) {\n1496:         updateAgent(state, agent.feature_id, {\n1497:           status: \"failed\",\n1498:           error: err.message,\n1499:           activity: null,\n1500:           completed_at: new Date().toISOString(),\n1501:         });\n1502:         saveState(projectRoot, state);\n1503:         wtLog(agent.feature_id, `SETUP FAILED: ${err.message.split(\"\\n\")[0]}`);\n1504:       }\n1505:     })\n1506:   );\n1507: \n1508:   const mux = detectMultiplexer(config.agent.multiplexer);\n1509:   const muxName = getMultiplexerName(config);\n1510:   if (fmt === \"text\") {\n1511:     console.log(\"\\nInteractive sessions launched. Use these commands:\");\n1512:     console.log(`  ${muxAttachCommand(mux, `${config.agent.tmuxPrefix}-<feature-id>`)}   # attach to a session`);\n1513:     console.log(`  ${muxListCommand(mux)}${\" \".repeat(Math.max(1, 54 - muxListCommand(mux).length))}# list sessions`);\n1514:     console.log(\"  woco status                                             # check status\");\n1515:     console.log(\"  woco verify                                             # verify builds\");\n1516:     console.log(\"  woco merge                                              # merge verified\");\n1517:     console.log(\"  woco cleanup                                            # remove worktrees\");\n1518: \n1519:     printDashboard(state);\n1520:   }\n1521: }\n1522: \n1523: // ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n1524: // Main Command\n1525: // ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n1526: \n1527: export async function cmdLaunch(opts: LaunchCommandOptions): Promise<void> {\n1528:   const { projectRoot } = opts;\n1529:   let { config } = opts;\n1530:   const fmt = opts.outputFmt ?? \"text\";\n1531: \n1532:   if (fmt === \"text\") console.log(\"\\n--- wombo-combo: Launch ---\\n\");\n1533: \n1534:   // Ensure agent definition exists — reinstall from template if missing\n1535:   ensureAgentDefinition(projectRoot, config, opts.agent);\n1536: \n1537:   // -------------------------------------------------------------------------\n1538:   // Quest resolution — if --quest was specified, scope the wave to that quest\n1539:   // -------------------------------------------------------------------------\n1540:   let questContext: QuestPromptContext | undefined;\n1541:   let questId: string | null = opts.questId ?? null;\n1542: \n1543:   if (questId) {\n1544:     const quest = loadQuest(projectRoot, questId);\n1545:     if (!quest) {\n1546:       outputError(fmt, `Quest \"${questId}\" not found. Use 'woco quest list' to see available quests.`);\n1547:       return; // unreachable\n1548:     }\n1549: \n1550:     if (quest.status !== \"active\") {\n1551:       outputError(fmt, `Quest \"${questId}\" is in status \"${quest.status}\" — only active quests can be launched. Use 'woco quest activate ${questId}' first.`);\n1552:       return; // unreachable\n1553:     }\n1554: \n1555:     // Ensure the quest branch exists (create from baseBranch if needed)\n1556:     if (!questBranchExists(projectRoot, questId)) {\n1557:       if (fmt === \"text\") console.log(`Creating quest branch \"${quest.branch}\" from \"${quest.baseBranch}\"...`);\n1558:       createQuestBranch(projectRoot, questId, quest.baseBranch);\n1559:     }\n1560: \n1561:     // Override baseBranch — task branches will fork from the quest branch\n1562:     opts.baseBranch = quest.branch;\n1563:     if (fmt === \"text\") {\n1564:       console.log(`Quest: ${quest.title} (${questId})`);\n1565:       console.log(`  Base branch overridden to: ${quest.branch}`);\n1566:     }\n1567: \n1568:     // Apply quest config overrides (layered on top of project config)\n1569:     config = resolveQuestConfig(config, quest);\n1570: \n1571:     // Build quest prompt context for agent prompts\n1572:     const knowledge = loadQuestKnowledge(projectRoot, questId);\n1573:     questContext = {\n1574:       questId: quest.id,\n1575:       goal: quest.goal,\n1576:       addedConstraints: quest.constraints.add ?? [],\n1577:       addedForbidden: quest.constraints.ban ?? [],\n1578:       knowledge,\n1579:     };\n1580: \n1581:     if (fmt === \"text\") {\n1582:       const constraintCount = questContext.addedConstraints.length + questContext.addedForbidden.length;\n1583:       if (constraintCount > 0) {\n1584:         console.log(`  Quest constraints: ${questContext.addedConstraints.length} added, ${questContext.addedForbidden.length} banned`);\n1585:       }\n1586:       if (knowledge) {\n1587:         console.log(`  Quest knowledge: loaded (${knowledge.length} bytes)`);\n1588:       }\n1589:       console.log(\"\");\n1590:     }\n1591:   }\n1592: \n1593:   // Extract HITL mode from quest (defaults to undefined / yolo for non-quest waves)\n1594:   const hitlMode = questId ? loadQuest(projectRoot, questId)?.hitlMode : undefined;\n1595: \n1596:   // Ensure portless proxy is running (if enabled) to prevent port collisions\n1597:   if (config.portless.enabled) {\n1598:     if (isPortlessAvailable(config)) {\n1599:       const proxyOk = ensureProxyRunning(config);\n1600:       if (!proxyOk && fmt === \"text\") {\n1601:         console.warn(\n1602:           \"\\x1b[33m[portless]\\x1b[0m proxy could not be started — agents may encounter port collisions\"\n1603:         );\n1604:       }\n1605:     } else if (fmt === \"text\") {\n1606:       console.warn(\n1607:         \"\\x1b[33m[portless]\\x1b[0m enabled but not installed. Install with: npm install -g portless\"\n1608:       );\n1609:       console.warn(\n1610:         \"  Agents will run without portless — concurrent dev servers may have port collisions.\\n\"\n1611:       );\n1612:     }\n1613:   }\n1614: \n1615:   // -------------------------------------------------------------------------\n1616:   // Validate that the configured baseBranch exists as a local branch\n1617:   // -------------------------------------------------------------------------\n1618:   if (!branchExists(projectRoot, opts.baseBranch)) {\n1619:     const msg = `Base branch \"${opts.baseBranch}\" does not exist as a local branch. ` +\n1620:       `Create it first (e.g. \"git checkout -b ${opts.baseBranch}\") or specify ` +\n1621:       `a different branch with --base-branch.`;\n1622:     outputError(fmt, msg);\n1623:   }\n1624: \n1625:   // -------------------------------------------------------------------------\n1626:   // Check for existing wave state — don't overwrite work in progress\n1627:   // -------------------------------------------------------------------------\n1628:   const existingState = loadState(projectRoot);\n1629:   if (existingState) {\n1630:     const merged = existingState.agents.filter((a) => a.status === \"merged\");\n1631:     const verified = existingState.agents.filter((a) => a.status === \"verified\");\n1632:     const completed = existingState.agents.filter((a) => a.status === \"completed\");\n1633:     const running = existingState.agents.filter((a) => a.status === \"running\");\n1634:     const queued = existingState.agents.filter((a) => a.status === \"queued\");\n1635:     const failed = existingState.agents.filter((a) => a.status === \"failed\");\n1636: \n1637:     const hasWork = merged.length > 0 || verified.length > 0 || completed.length > 0 || running.length > 0;\n1638: \n1639:     if (hasWork) {\n1640:       if (fmt === \"text\") {\n1641:         console.log(`Existing wave found: ${existingState.wave_id}`);\n1642:         console.log(`  ${merged.length} merged, ${verified.length} verified, ${completed.length} completed, ${running.length} running, ${queued.length} queued, ${failed.length} failed`);\n1643:       }\n1644: \n1645:       // Finalize any merged agents by marking their features as done\n1646:       const finalizedIds: string[] = [];\n1647:       if (merged.length > 0) {\n1648:         if (fmt === \"text\") console.log(\"\\nFinalizing merged tasks in tasks file...\");\n1649:         for (const agent of merged) {\n1650:           markFeatureDone(projectRoot, agent.feature_id, config, existingState.base_branch, fmt);\n1651:           finalizedIds.push(agent.feature_id);\n1652:           // Clean up worktree and branch (already merged, safe to delete)\n1653:           try {\n1654:             removeWorktree(projectRoot, agent.worktree, true);\n1655:             if (fmt === \"text\") console.log(`  ${agent.feature_id}: marked done, worktree removed`);\n1656:           } catch {\n1657:             if (fmt === \"text\") console.log(`  ${agent.feature_id}: marked done (worktree already cleaned)`);\n1658:           }\n1659:         }\n1660:       }\n1661: \n1662:       // Strip finalized task IDs from explicit selection so we don't\n1663:       // try to re-launch tasks that were just marked done\n1664:       if (finalizedIds.length > 0 && opts.features?.length) {\n1665:         const finalizedSet = new Set(finalizedIds);\n1666:         opts.features = opts.features.filter((id) => !finalizedSet.has(id));\n1667:       }\n1668: \n1669:       // Verified agents: build passed but NOT merged — do NOT mark done.\n1670:       // Leave them for 'woco resume' to attempt the merge.\n1671:       if (verified.length > 0) {\n1672:         for (const agent of verified) {\n1673:           if (fmt === \"text\") console.log(`  ${agent.feature_id}: verified (not yet merged) — use 'woco resume' to merge`);\n1674:         }\n1675:       }\n1676: \n1677:       const activeCount = running.length + completed.length + queued.length;\n1678:       if (activeCount > 0) {\n1679:         outputError(fmt, `Wave ${existingState.wave_id} has ${activeCount} unfinished agent(s). Use 'woco resume' to continue the existing wave, or 'woco cleanup' to clear it before starting a new one.`);\n1680:       }\n1681: \n1682:       // All agents are in terminal states (merged/verified/failed) — safe to start fresh\n1683:       if (fmt === \"text\") console.log(\"\\nAll agents in previous wave are finished. Starting fresh wave.\\n\");\n1684:     }\n1685:   }\n1686: \n1687:   // Load features\n1688:   const data = loadFeatures(projectRoot, config);\n1689: \n1690:   // Build selection options\n1691:   const selOpts: SelectionOptions = {};\n1692:   if (opts.topPriority) selOpts.topPriority = opts.topPriority;\n1693:   if (opts.quickestWins) selOpts.quickestWins = opts.quickestWins;\n1694:   if (opts.priority) selOpts.priority = opts.priority;\n1695:   if (opts.difficulty) selOpts.difficulty = opts.difficulty;\n1696:   if (opts.features) selOpts.taskIds = opts.features;\n1697:   if (opts.allReady) selOpts.allReady = true;\n1698: \n1699:   // Select features\n1700:   let selected = selectFeatures(data, selOpts);\n1701: \n1702:   if (selected.length === 0) {\n1703:     // Build a context-aware message based on which flags were passed\n1704:     const activeFilters: string[] = [];\n1705:     if (opts.allReady) activeFilters.push(\"--all-ready\");\n1706:     if (opts.topPriority) activeFilters.push(`--top-priority ${opts.topPriority}`);\n1707:     if (opts.quickestWins) activeFilters.push(`--quickest-wins ${opts.quickestWins}`);\n1708:     if (opts.priority) activeFilters.push(`--priority ${opts.priority}`);\n1709:     if (opts.difficulty) activeFilters.push(`--difficulty ${opts.difficulty}`);\n1710:     if (opts.features?.length) activeFilters.push(`--tasks ${opts.features.join(\",\")}`);\n1711: \n1712:     let msg: string;\n1713:     if (opts.allReady && activeFilters.length === 1) {\n1714:       msg = \"No launchable tasks found (all tasks are done, cancelled, or have unmet dependencies).\";\n1715:     } else if (activeFilters.length > 0) {\n1716:       msg = `No tasks matched the current filters: ${activeFilters.join(\", \")}.`;\n1717:     } else {\n1718:       msg = \"No launchable tasks found.\";\n1719:     }\n1720: \n1721:     // Throw instead of outputError so TUI callers can catch gracefully.\n1722:     // CLI callers catch this in the command handler (index.ts).\n1723:     throw new Error(msg);\n1724:   }\n1725: \n1726:   // Apply quest constraints to selected tasks (add/ban layered on each task)\n1727:   if (questId && questContext) {\n1728:     const quest = loadQuest(projectRoot, questId)!;\n1729:     selected = selected.map((f) => applyQuestConstraintsToTask(f, quest));\n1730:   }\n1731: \n1732:   // Show selection\n1733:   if (fmt === \"text\") {\n1734:     printFeatureSelection(\n1735:       selected.map((f) => ({\n1736:         id: f.id,\n1737:         title: f.title,\n1738:         priority: f.priority,\n1739:         difficulty: f.difficulty,\n1740:         effort: f.effort,\n1741:       }))\n1742:     );\n1743:   }\n1744: \n1745:   // Check per-task agent definitions exist\n1746:   if (!opts.agent) {\n1747:     const taskAgents = new Set(\n1748:       selected.map((f) => f.agent).filter((a): a is string => !!a)\n1749:     );\n1750:     for (const agentName of taskAgents) {\n1751:       ensureAgentDefinition(projectRoot, config, agentName);\n1752:     }\n1753:   }\n1754: \n1755:   // ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n1756:   // Dependency graph analysis\n1757:   // ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n1758:   const depGraph = buildDepGraph(selected, data.tasks);\n1759:   let schedulePlan: SchedulePlan | null = null;\n1760: \n1761:   // Check if any features actually have dependencies within the selected set\n1762:   const hasDeps = selected.some(\n1763:     (f) => f.depends_on.some((d) => selected.find((s) => s.id === d))\n1764:   );\n1765: \n1766:   if (hasDeps) {\n1767:     // Validate graph — throws on cycles or dangling deps\n1768:     try {\n1769:       validateDepGraph(depGraph);\n1770:     } catch (err: any) {\n1771:       outputError(fmt, `${err.message}\\nFix dependency issues before launching.`);\n1772:     }\n1773: \n1774:     // Build scheduling plan\n1775:     schedulePlan = buildSchedulePlan(depGraph);\n1776:     if (fmt === \"text\") console.log(`\\n${formatSchedulePlan(schedulePlan)}\\n`);\n1777:   }\n1778: \n1779:   if (opts.dryRun) {\n1780:     const dryRunResult = {\n1781:       dry_run: true,\n1782:       base_branch: opts.baseBranch,\n1783:       max_concurrent: opts.maxConcurrent,\n1784:       model: opts.model ?? null,\n1785:       interactive: opts.interactive,\n1786:       selected: selected.map((f) => ({\n1787:         id: f.id,\n1788:         title: f.title,\n1789:         priority: f.priority,\n1790:         difficulty: f.difficulty,\n1791:         effort: f.effort,\n1792:       })),\n1793:       schedule_plan: schedulePlan ? {\n1794:         streams: schedulePlan.streams.map((s) => s.featureIds),\n1795:         merge_gates: schedulePlan.mergeGates.map((g) => ({\n1796:           feature_id: g.featureId,\n1797:           wait_for: g.waitFor,\n1798:         })),\n1799:         topological_order: schedulePlan.topologicalOrder,\n1800:       } : null,\n1801:     };\n1802: \n1803:     output(fmt, dryRunResult, () => {\n1804:       console.log(\"Dry run — not launching agents.\");\n1805:     }, () => {\n1806:       console.log(renderLaunchDryRun(dryRunResult));\n1807:     });\n1808:     return;\n1809:   }\n1810: \n1811:   // ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n1812:   // Agent registry: resolve specialized agents for tasks with agent_type\n1813:   // ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n1814:   let agentResolutions: Map<string, AgentResolution> | undefined;\n1815: \n1816:   if (config.agentRegistry.mode !== \"disabled\") {\n1817:     const tasksWithAgentType = selected.filter((t) => t.agent_type);\n1818:     if (tasksWithAgentType.length > 0) {\n1819:       if (fmt === \"text\") console.log(`\\nResolving ${tasksWithAgentType.length} specialized agent(s) from registry...`);\n1820:       agentResolutions = await prepareAgentDefinitions(selected, config, projectRoot);\n1821: \n1822:       const specialized = [...agentResolutions.values()].filter(isSpecializedAgent);\n1823:       const cached = specialized.filter((r) => r.fromCache);\n1824:       if (fmt === \"text\") {\n1825:         console.log(\n1826:           `  ${specialized.length} specialized (${cached.length} cached, ${specialized.length - cached.length} fetched), ` +\n1827:           `${selected.length - specialized.length} generalist`\n1828:         );\n1829:       }\n1830:     }\n1831:   }\n1832: \n1833:   // ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n1834:   // Preflight confirmation\n1835:   // ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n1836:   if (agentResolutions && agentResolutions.size > 0) {\n1837:     const isTTY = process.stdout.isTTY && process.stdin.isTTY;\n1838:     const preflight = isTTY && !opts.noTui\n1839:       ? await tuiPreflightConfirm(selected, agentResolutions, config)\n1840:       : await consolePreflightConfirm(selected, agentResolutions, config);\n1841: \n1842:     if (!preflight.proceed) {\n1843:       outputMessage(fmt, \"Launch cancelled.\");\n1844:       return;\n1845:     }\n1846: \n1847:     // Apply user's changes (rejected agents, mode changes)\n1848:     agentResolutions = preflight.agents;\n1849:   }\n1850: \n1851:   // Create wave state\n1852:   const state = createWaveState({\n1853:     baseBranch: opts.baseBranch,\n1854:     maxConcurrent: opts.maxConcurrent,\n1855:     model: opts.model ?? null,\n1856:     interactive: opts.interactive,\n1857:     questId,\n1858:   });\n1859: \n1860:   // Store serialized schedule plan in wave state\n1861:   if (schedulePlan) {\n1862:     state.schedule_plan = {\n1863:       streams: schedulePlan.streams.map((s) => s.featureIds),\n1864:       merge_gates: schedulePlan.mergeGates.map((g) => ({\n1865:         feature_id: g.featureId,\n1866:         wait_for: g.waitFor,\n1867:       })),\n1868:       topological_order: schedulePlan.topologicalOrder,\n1869:     };\n1870:   }\n1871: \n1872:   // Create agent entries for all selected features\n1873:   const selectedIds = new Set(selected.map((f) => f.id));\n1874: \n1875:   // Build a map from feature ID → shared worktree path for chain reuse.\n1876:   // All features in the same chain share the worktree of the chain's first feature.\n1877:   const chainWorktreeMap = new Map<string, string>();\n1878:   if (schedulePlan) {\n1879:     for (const stream of schedulePlan.streams) {\n1880:       if (stream.featureIds.length > 1) {\n1881:         // All features in this chain share the first feature's worktree\n1882:         const sharedWtPath = worktreePath(projectRoot, stream.featureIds[0], config);\n1883:         for (const featureId of stream.featureIds) {\n1884:           chainWorktreeMap.set(featureId, sharedWtPath);\n1885:         }\n1886:       }\n1887:     }\n1888:   }\n1889: \n1890:   for (const feature of selected) {\n1891:     const branch = featureBranchName(feature.id, config);\n1892:     // Use shared worktree path for chain members, or individual path otherwise\n1893:     const wtPath = chainWorktreeMap.get(feature.id) ?? worktreePath(projectRoot, feature.id, config);\n1894:     const agent = createAgentState(feature.id, branch, wtPath, opts.maxRetries);\n1895: \n1896:     // Set effort estimate from feature spec\n1897:     const effortMinutes = parseDurationMinutes(feature.effort);\n1898:     agent.effort_estimate_ms = effortMinutes === Infinity ? null : effortMinutes * 60 * 1000;\n1899: \n1900:     // Populate dependency fields from the graph\n1901:     const graphNode = depGraph.nodes.get(feature.id);\n1902:     if (graphNode) {\n1903:       // Only track internal deps (within the selected set)\n1904:       agent.depends_on = graphNode.dependsOn.filter((d) => selectedIds.has(d));\n1905:       agent.depended_on_by = graphNode.dependedOnBy.filter((d) => selectedIds.has(d));\n1906:     }\n1907: \n1908:     // Set stream index\n1909:     if (schedulePlan) {\n1910:       agent.stream_index = getStreamForFeature(schedulePlan, feature.id);\n1911:     }\n1912: \n1913:     // Set specialized agent info from resolution\n1914:     const resolution = agentResolutions?.get(feature.id);\n1915:     if (resolution && isSpecializedAgent(resolution)) {\n1916:       agent.agent_name = resolution.name;\n1917:       agent.agent_type = resolution.agentType;\n1918:     }\n1919: \n1920:     // Per-task local agent override: CLI --agent flag takes precedence,\n1921:     // then task-level `agent` field, then registry resolution (above).\n1922:     // This is for local agent definitions in .opencode/agents/<name>.md.\n1923:     const localAgent = opts.agent ?? feature.agent;\n1924:     if (localAgent && !agent.agent_name) {\n1925:       // Only set if not already resolved from the external registry\n1926:       agent.agent_name = localAgent;\n1927:     } else if (opts.agent) {\n1928:       // CLI --agent flag overrides even registry agents\n1929:       agent.agent_name = opts.agent;\n1930:     }\n1931: \n1932:     state.agents.push(agent);\n1933:   }\n1934: \n1935:   saveState(projectRoot, state);\n1936:   if (fmt === \"text\") console.log(`Wave ${state.wave_id} created with ${selected.length} agents.`);\n1937: \n1938:   // Launch agents up to max_concurrent\n1939:   if (opts.interactive) {\n1940:     await launchWaveInteractive(projectRoot, state, selected, opts, agentResolutions, questContext, hitlMode);\n1941:   } else {\n1942:     await launchWaveHeadless(projectRoot, state, selected, opts, agentResolutions, questContext, hitlMode);\n1943:   }\n1944: }\n\n(End of file - total 1944 lines)\n</content>","title":"src/commands/launch.ts","metadata":{"preview":"  const { config, model } = opts;\n  const fmt = opts.outputFmt ?? \"text\";\n  const featureMap = new Map(features.map((f) => [f.id, f]));\n\n  // Show dashboard immediately\n  if (fmt === \"text\") printDashboard(state);\n\n  // Launch initial batch — parallelize setup\n  const tolaunch = queuedAgents(state).slice(0, opts.maxConcurrent);\n  if (fmt === \"text\") console.log(`Setting up ${tolaunch.length} agent(s) in parallel...\\n`);\n\n  await Promise.all(\n    tolaunch.map(async (agent) => {\n      updateAgent(state, agent.feature_id, {\n        status: \"installing\",\n        started_at: new Date().toISOString(),\n        activity: \"setting up worktree...\",\n      });\n      saveState(projectRoot, state);\n","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"time":{"start":1773483414052,"end":1773483414057}}}}
