{"type":"text","timestamp":1773483585725,"sessionID":"ses_31427856effefwaC38OEq6YCmn","part":{"id":"prt_cebdb8db1001s1y13vetJ9vDUL","sessionID":"ses_31427856effefwaC38OEq6YCmn","messageID":"msg_cebdb81c5001Bfdf7gyjNDIHGa","type":"text","text":"## Goal\n\nComplete the `wave-detach-audit` feature: audit the agent process lifecycle on monitor teardown in the wombo-combo project. Investigate whether agents spawned via `child_process.spawn` survive when the WomboTUI (wave monitor) screen is destroyed, document findings, and identify what needs changing.\n\n## Instructions\n\n- Use conventional commits with scope `wave-detach-audit`\n- Commit after each logical unit of work\n- Do NOT push to remote or modify `tasks` directory\n- Run `bun run build` to verify everything compiles before considering task complete\n- Always use `bun dev` (not global binary) when running wombo commands\n- Use `portless run` when starting any localhost server\n\n## Discoveries\n\n1. **Headless agents do NOT survive parent death** — All three headless spawn functions (`launchHeadless`, `retryHeadless`, `launchConflictResolver`) use `detached: false`, never call `unref()`, and pipe stdio. This is **intentional and correct** — piped stdout is required for `ProcessMonitor` to parse JSON events in real-time.\n\n2. **`ProcessMonitor.killAll()` DOES kill child processes** — It sends SIGTERM to all non-reconnected processes. Reconnected processes (from `reconnectProcess()`, typically mux-based agents) are intentionally NOT killed — just removed from the monitor map.\n\n3. **`screen.destroy()` does NOT affect agent processes** — `WomboTUI.stop()` only tears down the TUI. Agent termination is handled by the `onQuit` callback which calls `monitor.killAll()`. This separation is intentional because `stop()` is also called during temporary mux attach/detach.\n\n4. **Interactive mode agents survive naturally** — They run inside dmux/tmux sessions independent of the parent process.\n\n5. **Recovery mechanism exists** — `woco resume` handles recovery from ungraceful shutdowns by detecting orphaned worktrees with commits and re-verifying/re-launching.\n\n6. **No changes needed** — The current design is correct for both modes. The existing code already had partial inline audit annotations (tagged `wave-detach-audit`) in launcher.ts, monitor.ts, tui.ts, launch.ts, and resume.ts from prior work on main.\n\n## Accomplished\n\n**COMPLETED — All tasks done, build passes.**\n\n- ✅ Analyzed `launcher.ts`: agents spawned with `detached: false`, no `unref()`, piped stdio\n- ✅ Analyzed `monitor.ts`: `killAll()` sends SIGTERM to children, skips reconnected processes\n- ✅ Analyzed `tui.ts`: `screen.destroy()` does not affect agent processes\n- ✅ Verified existing inline audit documentation is accurate and complete\n- ✅ Added missing audit annotations to `launchWaveInteractive()` in launch.ts, `cleanup.ts` module header, `retry.ts` module header\n- ✅ Created centralized `PROCESS-LIFECYCLE.md` audit document with full findings\n- ✅ `bun run build` passes (1.31 MB bundle, 179 modules)\n- ✅ `bun run typecheck` passes (no errors)\n\n**2 commits on branch `feature/wave-detach-audit`:**\n1. `9502c55` — docs(wave-detach-audit): add audit annotations to interactive launch, cleanup, and retry\n2. `46785ef` — docs(wave-detach-audit): add centralized process lifecycle audit document\n\n## Relevant files / directories\n\n### Key files analyzed (read-only, already had audit annotations)\n- `src/lib/launcher.ts` — Agent spawn functions, `detached: false` configuration\n- `src/lib/monitor.ts` — `ProcessMonitor` class, `killAll()`, `remove()`, `reconnectProcess()`\n- `src/lib/tui.ts` — `WomboTUI` class, `start()`/`stop()` lifecycle, `onQuit` callback\n\n### Files modified (audit annotations added)\n- `src/commands/launch.ts` — Added audit comment to `launchWaveInteractive()` section\n- `src/commands/cleanup.ts` — Added process lifecycle section to module header JSDoc\n- `src/commands/retry.ts` — Added process lifecycle section to module header JSDoc\n\n### Files created\n- `PROCESS-LIFECYCLE.md` — Centralized audit document with all findings, shutdown flows, and recommendations\n\n### Files read for context\n- `src/commands/resume.ts` — Agent recovery triage logic (already had audit annotations)\n- `AGENTS.md` — Project coding conventions and workflow guidelines\n- `CONTEXT.md`, `README.md` — Project context","time":{"start":1773483585724,"end":1773483585724}}}
